00:01:54.790 --> 00:01:58.470 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: Exactly,
Portugale, yeah, I mean,

00:01:58.470 --> 00:02:00.780 align:middle line:84%
I thought the story
about the Templar

00:02:00.780 --> 00:02:03.450 align:middle line:90%
should be with the Templars.

00:02:03.450 --> 00:02:05.610 align:middle line:84%
I had no idea that
the real story

00:02:05.610 --> 00:02:09.030 align:middle line:84%
lies in understanding
Bernard of Clairvaux.

00:02:09.030 --> 00:02:12.510 align:middle line:10%
Once you understand him-- and
I've read 500 of his surviving

00:02:12.510 --> 00:02:15.960 align:middle line:10%
letters, to the point where I
kind of got under his skin--

00:02:15.960 --> 00:02:18.220 align:middle line:10%
to find out that this
guy was extraordinary.

00:02:18.220 --> 00:02:22.460 align:middle line:10%
I mean, he was a renaissance man
who was technically Catholic,

00:02:22.460 --> 00:02:24.310 align:middle line:10%
although he paid the
church lip service.

00:02:24.310 --> 00:02:26.670 align:middle line:10%
He was a great diplomat.

00:02:26.670 --> 00:02:27.840 align:middle line:10%
He was a great healer.

00:02:27.840 --> 00:02:30.660 align:middle line:10%
And his whole concept
was to try and bring back

00:02:30.660 --> 00:02:33.990 align:middle line:10%
Christianity to its original
and true roots, which is not

00:02:33.990 --> 00:02:36.420 align:middle line:10%
to do with Jesus, but to do
with John the Baptist and Mary

00:02:36.420 --> 00:02:37.460 align:middle line:10%
Magdalene.

00:02:37.460 --> 00:02:39.060 align:middle line:84%
And he was a great
supporter of both.

00:02:39.060 --> 00:02:41.480 align:middle line:84%
But he paid lip service
to the Catholic church.

00:02:41.480 --> 00:02:44.980 align:middle line:84%
So he was fed up with
the wonderful lifestyle

00:02:44.980 --> 00:02:46.710 align:middle line:84%
that the church
people were having

00:02:46.710 --> 00:02:49.200 align:middle line:90%
at the expense of the peasants.

00:02:49.200 --> 00:02:52.050 align:middle line:84%
He was afraid that the
Benedictine order was also

00:02:52.050 --> 00:02:55.470 align:middle line:84%
too corrupt and too, you know,
full-bellied for its own good.

00:02:55.470 --> 00:02:57.880 align:middle line:84%
And he said, this is not what
real Christianity is about.

00:02:57.880 --> 00:02:59.070 align:middle line:90%
It's about asceticism.

00:02:59.070 --> 00:03:01.980 align:middle line:84%
It's about spirituality and
being a beacon to others,

00:03:01.980 --> 00:03:04.470 align:middle line:84%
to raise them from their
level, you know, obviously,

00:03:04.470 --> 00:03:05.850 align:middle line:90%
trying to survive.

00:03:05.850 --> 00:03:09.210 align:middle line:84%
Bernard essentially
forms a splinter group

00:03:09.210 --> 00:03:12.630 align:middle line:84%
called the Cistercian
Order, the Order of Cister.

00:03:12.630 --> 00:03:15.780 align:middle line:10%
And it turns out that
this order was also

00:03:15.780 --> 00:03:18.840 align:middle line:10%
backed by the people
called the Order of Sion

00:03:18.840 --> 00:03:20.310 align:middle line:10%
back in Burgundy--

00:03:20.310 --> 00:03:24.780 align:middle line:10%
so again, interchanging
relationships going on here.

00:03:24.780 --> 00:03:29.517 align:middle line:84%
And the moment that
he actually finds out

00:03:29.517 --> 00:03:31.350 align:middle line:84%
that there's a window
of opportunity to send

00:03:31.350 --> 00:03:34.050 align:middle line:84%
a few people over to
Jerusalem to dig up something

00:03:34.050 --> 00:03:37.950 align:middle line:84%
on the Temple Mount, he
sends some of his own monks

00:03:37.950 --> 00:03:40.620 align:middle line:84%
to Jerusalem, who then
become the Knights Templar.

00:03:40.620 --> 00:03:42.880 align:middle line:84%
So the Templars
aren't just Templars.

00:03:42.880 --> 00:03:45.930 align:middle line:84%
They are also members
of the Cistercian Order,

00:03:45.930 --> 00:03:48.640 align:middle line:84%
and some of them are also
members of the Order of Sion.

00:03:48.640 --> 00:03:51.360 align:middle line:84%
So these three organizations
are essentially

00:03:51.360 --> 00:03:54.600 align:middle line:84%
the groups that become the
central characters who are now

00:03:54.600 --> 00:03:56.100 align:middle line:90%
known as the Knights Templar.

00:03:56.100 --> 00:04:00.470 align:middle line:84%
And eventually, they meander
over on boats in about 1125

00:04:00.470 --> 00:04:03.420 align:middle line:84%
with a big secret and a mandate
by Hughes De Payens to go,

00:04:03.420 --> 00:04:07.210 align:middle line:84%
and I quote, "to establish
the crown of Portugal."

00:04:07.210 --> 00:04:09.450 align:middle line:84%
And this is, you know, the
biggest overlooked story

00:04:09.450 --> 00:04:11.820 align:middle line:84%
in European history,
the creation of Europe's

00:04:11.820 --> 00:04:15.660 align:middle line:84%
first independent
nation-state by the Templars,

00:04:15.660 --> 00:04:18.420 align:middle line:84%
by the order of Sion,
and the Order of Cister,

00:04:18.420 --> 00:04:21.029 align:middle line:84%
who essentially put up
a monastery literally

00:04:21.029 --> 00:04:23.550 align:middle line:84%
within a year of the
Templars becoming official,

00:04:23.550 --> 00:04:27.060 align:middle line:84%
even though by the time they
became official in 1118,

00:04:27.060 --> 00:04:29.430 align:middle line:84%
they had already been in
Portugal for seven years.

00:04:29.430 --> 00:04:30.630 align:middle line:90%
They were given a castle.

00:04:30.630 --> 00:04:32.470 align:middle line:84%
Again, not many
people know this,

00:04:32.470 --> 00:04:35.310 align:middle line:84%
which tells us that the Templars
are much older than we ever

00:04:35.310 --> 00:04:36.180 align:middle line:90%
believed.

00:04:36.180 --> 00:04:38.340 align:middle line:84%
And that's what makes
this story fascinating.

00:04:38.340 --> 00:04:41.460 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: OK, now let's go
back another thousand years,

00:04:41.460 --> 00:04:44.130 align:middle line:84%
just to capture this one
statement by Julius Caesar

00:04:44.130 --> 00:04:47.579 align:middle line:84%
because, again, I really dug
through your book, Freddy.

00:04:47.579 --> 00:04:48.870 align:middle line:90%
Every single page is dog-eared.

00:04:48.870 --> 00:04:50.460 align:middle line:90%
That's why I'm so lost.

00:04:50.460 --> 00:04:52.350 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: How did Julius Caesar
get involved with the Templars?

00:04:52.350 --> 00:04:53.308 align:middle line:90%
You won't believe this.

00:04:53.308 --> 00:04:53.677 align:middle line:90%


00:04:53.677 --> 00:04:55.510 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: No, it's a
statement that he made.

00:04:55.510 --> 00:04:56.509 align:middle line:90%
And I want to read that.

00:04:56.509 --> 00:04:59.160 align:middle line:84%
It says, "there
exists a civilization

00:04:59.160 --> 00:05:01.650 align:middle line:84%
