confines of Iberia

00:05:01.650 --> 00:05:05.670 align:middle line:84%
who refuses to govern itself
and who refuses to be governed."

00:05:05.670 --> 00:05:06.470 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Yes.

00:05:06.470 --> 00:05:08.760 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: OK, you take it away.

00:05:08.760 --> 00:05:11.130 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: The original
people who settled

00:05:11.130 --> 00:05:13.680 align:middle line:84%
in what is today Northern
Spain and, of course,

00:05:13.680 --> 00:05:15.740 align:middle line:84%
Portugal were called
the Lusitanians.

00:05:15.740 --> 00:05:18.060 align:middle line:84%
It literally means those
who hold the light.

00:05:18.060 --> 00:05:22.530 align:middle line:84%
And they go back to a group
of traveling magician-gods

00:05:22.530 --> 00:05:25.530 align:middle line:84%
who escape a sinking island
in the middle of the Atlantic

00:05:25.530 --> 00:05:26.905 align:middle line:90%
about 11,000 years ago.

00:05:26.905 --> 00:05:30.540 align:middle line:84%
And they were very tall,
strangely long-handed,

00:05:30.540 --> 00:05:33.510 align:middle line:84%
and they deposited some very
interesting sacred places,

00:05:33.510 --> 00:05:36.060 align:middle line:84%
dedicated to the divine
virgin, in Portugal,

00:05:36.060 --> 00:05:38.080 align:middle line:84%
and then they moved
towards the Basque area.

00:05:38.080 --> 00:05:38.880 align:middle line:90%
And they went AWOL.

00:05:38.880 --> 00:05:41.060 align:middle line:84%
No one knows what
happened to them.

00:05:41.060 --> 00:05:42.790 align:middle line:84%
And from this, you
get the vestiges

00:05:42.790 --> 00:05:45.720 align:middle line:84%
of this independent
culture in Portugal

00:05:45.720 --> 00:05:48.000 align:middle line:84%
who basically paid
lip service to anyone

00:05:48.000 --> 00:05:50.112 align:middle line:84%
who came in and
told them, you know,

00:05:50.112 --> 00:05:51.820 align:middle line:84%
this is what you're
supposed to be doing.

00:05:51.820 --> 00:05:53.010 align:middle line:90%
They said, I'm sorry.

00:05:53.010 --> 00:05:54.135 align:middle line:90%
We're not going to do that.

00:05:54.135 --> 00:05:56.737 align:middle line:84%
And especially the church, they
were no friends of the church.

00:05:56.737 --> 00:05:57.570 align:middle line:90%
And they said, look.

00:05:57.570 --> 00:06:00.360 align:middle line:84%
The whole point of living
properly is to, you know,

00:06:00.360 --> 00:06:04.040 align:middle line:84%
rule over nobody and to not
be ruled by anybody else.

00:06:04.040 --> 00:06:06.570 align:middle line:84%
So it's a right of
self-determination to respect

00:06:06.570 --> 00:06:10.330 align:middle line:84%
others, which is actually the
true Christian brotherhood.

00:06:10.330 --> 00:06:11.850 align:middle line:90%
You know, love thy neighbor.

00:06:11.850 --> 00:06:13.650 align:middle line:90%
It's not that difficult, really.

00:06:13.650 --> 00:06:15.775 align:middle line:84%
So they didn't
rule over anybody.

00:06:15.775 --> 00:06:17.650 align:middle line:84%
They didn't want to be
ruled by anybody else.

00:06:17.650 --> 00:06:19.590 align:middle line:84%
So Julius Caesar found
it really difficult

00:06:19.590 --> 00:06:21.430 align:middle line:84%
to infiltrate that
part of the world.

00:06:21.430 --> 00:06:24.030 align:middle line:84%
And I think that's one of the
reasons why the Templars were

00:06:24.030 --> 00:06:27.530 align:middle line:84%
so adamant on having that
piece of real estate,

00:06:27.530 --> 00:06:29.850 align:middle line:84%
not only because it
was as far from Rome

00:06:29.850 --> 00:06:31.867 align:middle line:90%
as possible in the Middle Ages--

00:06:31.867 --> 00:06:33.450 align:middle line:84%
so they can go in
and do whatever they

00:06:33.450 --> 00:06:34.950 align:middle line:90%
wanted in complete secrecy--

00:06:34.950 --> 00:06:38.790 align:middle line:84%
but because there was a rich
history of heresy and people

00:06:38.790 --> 00:06:41.760 align:middle line:84%
who really wanted to do the
right thing spiritually.

00:06:41.760 --> 00:06:44.434 align:middle line:84%
And, of course, a heretic,
in its original term--

00:06:44.434 --> 00:06:45.725 align:middle line:90%
you're going to laugh at this--

00:06:45.725 --> 00:06:48.150 align:middle line:84%
a heretic is someone in
possession of the facts

00:06:48.150 --> 00:06:50.050 align:middle line:90%
who is able to choose.

00:06:50.050 --> 00:06:51.950 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Oh, that's
a better definition.

00:06:51.950 --> 00:06:52.840 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: It's the
original definition.

00:06:52.840 --> 00:06:53.360 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Seeing as how--

00:06:53.360 --> 00:06:54.170 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Isn't that funny?

00:06:54.170 --> 00:06:55.650 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: --hundreds of
thousands of heretics

00:06:55.650 --> 00:06:56.190 align:middle line:90%
were killed.

00:06:56.190 --> 00:06:57.600 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: Yeah, so if
someone calls you a heretic,

00:06:57.600 --> 00:06:58.770 align:middle line:90%
you'll say, actually, yes.

00:06:58.770 --> 00:07:00.061 align:middle line:90%
I do have a lot of information.

00:07:00.061 --> 00:07:01.200 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: I am, yes.

00:07:01.200 --> 00:07:02.730 align:middle line:84%
What's interesting
in this, Freddy,

00:07:02.730 --> 00:07:05.760 align:middle line:84%
is that according
to the hermetics,

00:07:05.760 --> 00:07:09.330 align:middle line:84%
one of the last remaining
visible remnants of Atlantis

00:07:09.330 --> 00:07:12.760 align:middle line:84%
