called people of the serpent.

00:07:47.700 --> 00:07:48.090 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yes.

00:07:48.090 --> 00:07:48.630 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: The [NON-ENGLISH].

00:07:48.630 --> 00:07:49.845 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:07:49.845 --> 00:07:51.810 align:middle line:84%
Another misunderstanding
of what the word

00:07:51.810 --> 00:07:53.250 align:middle line:90%
"serpent" and symbolism means.

00:07:53.250 --> 00:07:55.050 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: Energy,
it's energy currents.

00:07:55.050 --> 00:07:57.090 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Energy, the
movement of energy, again.

00:07:57.090 --> 00:07:58.890 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: The manipulation
of it and how to use it

00:07:58.890 --> 00:07:59.790 align:middle line:90%
for spiritual purposes.

00:07:59.790 --> 00:08:00.195 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Right.

00:08:00.195 --> 00:08:00.995 align:middle line:90%
I know.

00:08:00.995 --> 00:08:03.699 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: It makes perfect sense
why a group of mystic Templar

00:08:03.699 --> 00:08:06.240 align:middle line:84%
Knights would then move to this
particular part of the world,

00:08:06.240 --> 00:08:07.660 align:middle line:84%
because they already
had a rich history

00:08:07.660 --> 00:08:08.350 align:middle line:90%
with this understanding.

00:08:08.350 --> 00:08:10.070 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: They already
had that, absolutely.

00:08:10.070 --> 00:08:11.400 align:middle line:84%
But we were talking
off camera, and you

00:08:11.400 --> 00:08:13.050 align:middle line:84%
said there's
another place that's

00:08:13.050 --> 00:08:15.120 align:middle line:84%
little known, that
it's also thought

00:08:15.120 --> 00:08:16.860 align:middle line:90%
to be a remnant of Atlantis.

00:08:16.860 --> 00:08:17.790 align:middle line:90%
Just tease us.

00:08:17.790 --> 00:08:18.410 align:middle line:90%
Tell us.

00:08:18.410 --> 00:08:18.930 align:middle line:90%
Don't tease us.

00:08:18.930 --> 00:08:19.460 align:middle line:90%
Tell us.

00:08:19.460 --> 00:08:21.180 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: Yeah, it was
something that not many people

00:08:21.180 --> 00:08:21.980 align:middle line:90%
know about.

00:08:21.980 --> 00:08:24.815 align:middle line:84%
And it came about as a
result of a conversation

00:08:24.815 --> 00:08:26.190 align:middle line:84%
with a good friend
of mine who is

00:08:26.190 --> 00:08:28.190 align:middle line:84%
one of the most respected
psychics in the world,

00:08:28.190 --> 00:08:30.860 align:middle line:84%
I mean, someone who really
understands psychic ability,

00:08:30.860 --> 00:08:34.770 align:middle line:84%
who even the police in Britain
still use to this very day

00:08:34.770 --> 00:08:36.190 align:middle line:90%
to solve crimes.

00:08:36.190 --> 00:08:39.039 align:middle line:84%
And when I began on this
journey to look at the Templars

00:08:39.039 --> 00:08:41.580 align:middle line:84%
and look at the history of that
particular part of the world,

00:08:41.580 --> 00:08:43.020 align:middle line:84%
just said, well,
you really should

00:08:43.020 --> 00:08:47.250 align:middle line:84%
go to this particular
promontory near Sintra

00:08:47.250 --> 00:08:50.460 align:middle line:84%
because there's a vestige
of a citadel there

00:08:50.460 --> 00:08:53.562 align:middle line:84%
that collapsed into the ocean
when big tidal waves came over

00:08:53.562 --> 00:08:55.395 align:middle line:84%
from the Atlantic, from
a sinking continent,

00:08:55.395 --> 00:08:56.625 align:middle line:90%
and wiped it out.

00:08:56.625 --> 00:08:58.860 align:middle line:84%
It turns out that's
exactly where I was born.

00:08:58.860 --> 00:08:59.680 align:middle line:90%
So I went there.

00:08:59.680 --> 00:09:01.388 align:middle line:84%
And if you just go
off the beaten tourist

00:09:01.388 --> 00:09:04.790 align:middle line:84%
track down this cliff, there
is the remains of a road.

00:09:04.790 --> 00:09:07.400 align:middle line:84%
And quite clearly, there's
part of a big structure there.

00:09:07.400 --> 00:09:09.441 align:middle line:84%
And the rest of it, you
can see that it slid down

00:09:09.441 --> 00:09:10.350 align:middle line:90%
into the ocean.

00:09:10.350 --> 00:09:12.600 align:middle line:84%
The currents are very
strong there, very hard

00:09:12.600 --> 00:09:15.370 align:middle line:84%
to take any kind of
equipment to see properly.

00:09:15.370 --> 00:09:17.694 align:middle line:84%
But, yes, the citadel
is still there.

00:09:17.694 --> 00:09:19.860 align:middle line:84%
And it's in the folklore
that there were people here

00:09:19.860 --> 00:09:21.810 align:middle line:84%
that came from a
different continent,

00:09:21.810 --> 00:09:24.620 align:middle line:84%
because back then Portugal was
also part of a big landmass,

00:09:24.620 --> 00:09:26.580 align:middle line:84%
like the Sahara was
part of the ocean.

00:09:26.580 --> 00:09:29.684 align:middle line:84%
So our understanding of
where Atlantis was, we really

00:09:29.684 --> 00:09:31.600 align:middle line:84%
have little understanding
because the landmass

00:09:31.600 --> 00:09:32.680 align:middle line:90%
is so different today.

00:09:32.680 --> 00:09:34.770 align:middle line:84%
So that was part of
one little outpost.

00:09:34.770 --> 00:09:37.590 align:middle line:84%
And we do have in Portugal
some of the oldest sacred sites

00:09:37.590 --> 00:09:38.430 align:middle line:90%
in Europe.

00:09:38.430 --> 00:09:40.350 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: True, and when
people think of Atlantis,

00:09:40.350 --> 00:09:42.640 align:middle line:84%
they're only looking at
usually the final phase, which

00:09:42.640 --> 00:09:46.440 align:middle line:84%
was the smallest portion, after
the others had broken off,

00:09:46.440 --> 00:09:49.620 align:middle line:84%
sunken and so forth, to the
north, with very high culture,

00:09:49.620 --> 00:09:51.510 align:middle line:84%
even, you know,
hundreds, thousands

00:09:51.510 --> 00:09:53.290 align:middle line:90%
of years prior to that even.

00:09:53.290 --> 00:09:55.362 align:middle line:84%
So we have a real
misunderstanding in that way--

00:09:55.362 --> 00:09:56.320 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Oh, god, yeah.

00:09:56.320 --> 00:09:57.570 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: --you know,
how history is running.

00:09:57.570 --> 00:09:58.450 align:middle line:90%
But you brought up something.

00:09:58.450 --> 00:09:59.610 align:middle line:90%
You're from that area.

00:09:59.610 --> 00:10:05.280 align:middle line:84%
And I would say that you are
one of these people, right?

00:10:05.280 --> 00:10:08.430 align:middle line:84%
Obviously, you have taken
a huge chunk of your life

00:10:08.430 --> 00:10:11.820 align:middle line:84%
to invest yourself
into digging up

00:10:11.820 --> 00:10:13.510 align:middle line:84%
the truth behind
what the Templar were

00:10:13.510 --> 00:10:15.310 align:middle line:90%
and what they were upholding.

00:10:15.310 --> 00:10:15.850 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Can you keep a secret?

00:10:15.850 --> 00:10:17.641 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I believe
you were also in Egypt.

00:10:17.641 --> 00:10:20.540 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I think that you
are one of the players who

00:10:20.540 --> 00:10:23.600 align:middle line:84%
has come back throughout
history to bring us

00:10:23.600 --> 00:10:26.960 align:middle line:84%
these pieces of information
for our understanding,

00:10:26.960 --> 00:10:29.580 align:middle line:84%
so we can tap back into
our own higher forces.

00:10:29.580 --> 00:10:31.640 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: I've always
wondered why I'm 6 foot 5,

00:10:31.640 --> 00:10:32.570 align:middle line:90%
and I'm Portuguese.

00:10:32.570 --> 00:10:34.153 align:middle line:84%
You don't get the
two coming together.

00:10:34.153 --> 00:10:35.002 align:middle line:90%
So who knows?

00:10:35.002 --> 00:10:38.930 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: No, I
mean, I know you.

00:10:38.930 --> 00:10:40.160 align:middle line:90%
I've seen you a lot of times.

00:10:40.160 --> 00:10:43.350 align:middle line:84%
And I have identified
you, too, from other eras.

00:10:43.350 --> 00:10:47.060 align:middle line:84%
So I just want to
say that while we're

00:10:47.060 --> 00:10:49.520 align:middle line:84%
doing this interview because
you are one of the people that

00:10:49.520 --> 00:10:53.030 align:middle line:84%
comes back repeatedly and tries
to bring back the knowledge.

00:10:53.030 --> 00:10:54.125 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: You'd think I would
have learned the first time

00:10:54.125 --> 00:10:55.100 align:middle line:90%
to go somewhere else.

00:10:55.100 --> 00:10:56.599 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You're a
slow learner, OK?

00:10:56.599 --> 00:10:57.671 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:10:57.671 --> 00:10:58.149 align:middle line:90%


00:10:58.149 --> 00:10:59.690 align:middle line:84%
Smart, but a slow
learner, all right.

00:10:59.690 --> 00:11:01.190 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: Are there
any other planets

00:11:01.190 --> 00:11:03.290 align:middle line:84%
that look just like this,
though less troublesome?

00:11:03.290 --> 00:11:04.910 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I just thought
it's worth putting that out

00:11:04.910 --> 00:11:06.350 align:middle line:90%
so we can see this in context.

00:11:06.350 --> 00:11:07.824 align:middle line:90%
You know of which you speak.

00:11:07.824 --> 00:11:09.740 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: I actually
believe in that very much.

00:11:09.740 --> 00:11:12.122 align:middle line:84%
I think there are
people that go around,

00:11:12.122 --> 00:11:13.580 align:middle line:84%
people that I
respect as well, that

00:11:13.580 --> 00:11:16.220 align:middle line:84%
seem to be following
on from a tradition

00:11:16.220 --> 00:11:18.890 align:middle line:84%
that they didn't finish
the job the first time

00:11:18.890 --> 00:11:21.110 align:middle line:84%
around, for whatever reason,
because sometimes you're

00:11:21.110 --> 00:11:23.526 align:middle line:84%
hardwired with information
that you really shouldn't have.

00:11:23.526 --> 00:11:25.990 align:middle line:84%
Or you have a perception
way beyond your years.

00:11:25.990 --> 00:11:28.550 align:middle line:84%
I was drawing pyramids
when I was three.

00:11:28.550 --> 00:11:31.700 align:middle line:84%
I actually believed when I was
four that I had a pet dinosaur.

00:11:31.700 --> 00:11:33.540 align:middle line:90%
And we now know from strata.

00:11:33.540 --> 00:11:34.550 align:middle line:90%
I think it's in Texas.

00:11:34.550 --> 00:11:36.845 align:middle line:84%
You find human footprints
next to dinosaur prints.

00:11:36.845 --> 00:11:37.928 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Absolutely, yes.

00:11:37.928 --> 00:11:40.520 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: And I'm thinking, for
me, it's never been a big deal.

00:11:40.520 --> 00:11:41.686 align:middle line:90%
I've always understood that.

00:11:41.686 --> 00:11:44.100 align:middle line:84%
So it does make you wonder
where you fit into the bigger

00:11:44.100 --> 00:11:44.900 align:middle line:90%
scheme of things.

00:11:44.900 --> 00:11:47.090 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: But, you know,
it takes people like you

00:11:47.090 --> 00:11:48.500 align:middle line:84%
and others that
are on the planet

00:11:48.500 --> 00:11:54.740 align:middle line:84%
right now to come back and
not only thread it together.

00:11:54.740 --> 00:11:57.800 align:middle line:84%
There's something more than
that because within, you're

00:11:57.800 --> 00:12:00.470 align:middle line:84%
carrying forward
these native energies.

00:12:00.470 --> 00:12:03.590 align:middle line:84%
And they have a certain
attractant with them, right,

00:12:03.590 --> 00:12:07.050 align:middle line:84%
I mean, a magnetic pull
toward the information.

00:12:07.050 --> 00:12:10.940 align:middle line:84%
And oftentimes, these people
end up in positions of profile.

00:12:10.940 --> 00:12:14.290 align:middle line:84%
They can be in any industry,
but start attracting something

00:12:14.290 --> 00:12:15.090 align:middle line:90%
back.

00:12:15.090 --> 00:12:17.150 align:middle line:84%
But usually, you
can identify them

00:12:17.150 --> 00:12:21.980 align:middle line:84%
because they're bringing back
this kind of essential light.

00:12:21.980 --> 00:12:23.510 align:middle line:84%
You can see it or
feel the light.

00:12:23.510 --> 00:12:25.010 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes,
you'll even hear them

00:12:25.010 --> 00:12:27.380 align:middle line:84%
start dropping terms
and words, even if it's

00:12:27.380 --> 00:12:29.900 align:middle line:84%
an actor or a singer,
you know, that

00:12:29.900 --> 00:12:34.400 align:middle line:84%
have to do with their deep past
because we are no longer run

00:12:34.400 --> 00:12:36.320 align:middle line:90%
under, by and large--

00:12:36.320 --> 00:12:38.300 align:middle line:84%
I mean, OK, your
people in England,

00:12:38.300 --> 00:12:41.700 align:middle line:84%
anyway, normally, we're not
run under a system of royalty

00:12:41.700 --> 00:12:42.500 align:middle line:90%
anymore.

00:12:42.500 --> 00:12:45.620 align:middle line:84%
We're more rogue than
that as a species.

00:12:45.620 --> 00:12:48.140 align:middle line:84%
And so our cultural
icons are the leaders.

00:12:48.140 --> 00:12:50.610 align:middle line:84%
So they're the ones that have
to, the authors and poets.

00:12:50.610 --> 00:12:57.200 align:middle line:84%
And this is where bringing
hardcore evidence, science

00:12:57.200 --> 00:13:00.740 align:middle line:84%
melded with what you're
talking about from the psychic,

00:13:00.740 --> 00:13:05.300 align:middle line:84%
bringing it back with
intuitive remembrances,

00:13:05.300 --> 00:13:07.847 align:middle line:84%
is going to be the thing that
will piece our past together.

00:13:07.847 --> 00:13:08.930 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: I think so, yeah.

00:13:08.930 --> 00:13:10.620 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: It's not going to
come through science alone.

00:13:10.620 --> 00:13:11.120 align:middle line:90%
It can't.

00:13:11.120 --> 00:13:11.540 align:middle line:90%
It's too limited.

00:13:11.540 --> 00:13:13.331 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: Yeah, I think
it's an amalgamation

00:13:13.331 --> 00:13:14.690 align:middle line:90%
of different disciplines.

00:13:14.690 --> 00:13:15.430 align:middle line:84%
I think that's what
brings it together.

00:13:15.430 --> 00:13:15.870 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Exactly.

00:13:15.870 --> 00:13:18.161 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: I was having the
same conversation with Robert

00:13:18.161 --> 00:13:19.078 align:middle line:90%
Schoch, the geologist.

00:13:19.078 --> 00:13:21.161 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yes, he and I
talked about this as well.

00:13:21.161 --> 00:13:22.940 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: [INAUDIBLE]
the Sphinx, and just,

00:13:22.940 --> 00:13:24.650 align:middle line:84%
you know, having a
little conversation.

00:13:24.650 --> 00:13:26.630 align:middle line:84%
And it's like, yeah, the
more you actually see things

00:13:26.630 --> 00:13:28.046 align:middle line:84%
from other people's
point of view,

00:13:28.046 --> 00:13:30.020 align:middle line:84%
from different disciplines,
now you can start

00:13:30.020 --> 00:13:32.030 align:middle line:90%
bringing a picture together.

00:13:32.030 --> 00:13:33.810 align:middle line:84%
Archeology, yeah,
it has its flaws,

00:13:33.810 --> 00:13:35.710 align:middle line:90%
but it also has its good points.

00:13:35.710 --> 00:13:37.597 align:middle line:90%
And geology adds its portion.

00:13:37.597 --> 00:13:38.930 align:middle line:90%
Historians add a little portion.

00:13:38.930 --> 00:13:41.610 align:middle line:84%
The more open-minded you are
of sharing and seeing that

00:13:41.610 --> 00:13:44.330 align:middle line:84%
actually the thread, if you
link these different disciplines

00:13:44.330 --> 00:13:46.560 align:middle line:84%
together, from different
points of view,

00:13:46.560 --> 00:13:48.682 align:middle line:84%
now you have a better
picture and understanding.

00:13:48.682 --> 00:13:51.140 align:middle line:84%
That's why it takes so long to
write a good book, you know.

00:13:51.140 --> 00:13:53.660 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Exactly, but if you
allow the intuitive viewpoint

00:13:53.660 --> 00:13:55.329 align:middle line:84%
to come in as
well, you can start

00:13:55.329 --> 00:13:56.870 align:middle line:84%
getting some connective
tissue that's

00:13:56.870 --> 00:13:58.200 align:middle line:90%
missing sometimes in science.

00:13:58.200 --> 00:13:59.450 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Oh, it's much easier.

00:13:59.450 --> 00:14:00.950 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You know, it
makes it a lot easier, yes.

00:14:00.950 --> 00:14:01.610 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Shortcut.

00:14:01.610 --> 00:14:02.075 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah, exactly.

00:14:02.075 --> 00:14:04.760 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: The hard part is
then writing these things down

00:14:04.760 --> 00:14:07.310 align:middle line:84%
and then saying, how the hell
am I going to prove this?

00:14:07.310 --> 00:14:09.520 align:middle line:84%
And suddenly, stuff comes
out of the woodwork.

00:14:09.520 --> 00:14:10.936 align:middle line:90%
Books fall out of shelves.

00:14:10.936 --> 00:14:14.450 align:middle line:84%
And in my case, it literally was
the case, finding unusual books

00:14:14.450 --> 00:14:16.340 align:middle line:90%
and going, my God.

00:14:16.340 --> 00:14:18.470 align:middle line:90%
I remember swearing in Harvard.

00:14:18.470 --> 00:14:21.140 align:middle line:84%
You know, page 683 of
this massive book written

00:14:21.140 --> 00:14:22.700 align:middle line:90%
by Cistercian monks, I went--

00:14:22.700 --> 00:14:25.580 align:middle line:90%


00:14:25.580 --> 00:14:26.790 align:middle line:90%
and everybody turns around.

00:14:26.790 --> 00:14:27.590 align:middle line:90%
And I went, sorry.

00:14:27.590 --> 00:14:28.050 align:middle line:90%


