Back then, it was
nothing more than--

00:15:52.380 --> 00:15:54.840 align:middle line:84%
it was based around the
town of what today is called

00:15:54.840 --> 00:15:57.090 align:middle line:90%
Porto, a very small place.

00:15:57.090 --> 00:15:59.790 align:middle line:84%
And they basically helped
the local king get rid

00:15:59.790 --> 00:16:01.870 align:middle line:90%
of a lot of unfriendly people.

00:16:01.870 --> 00:16:04.920 align:middle line:84%
And the knight was rewarded
with a piece of land, a dowry,

00:16:04.920 --> 00:16:07.790 align:middle line:84%
and, of course, a
lovely princess,

00:16:07.790 --> 00:16:09.780 align:middle line:84%
which he puts to good
use because he builds

00:16:09.780 --> 00:16:13.140 align:middle line:84%
a little place called
the County of Portugale,

00:16:13.140 --> 00:16:16.740 align:middle line:84%
turns it into this
wonderful, little paradise,

00:16:16.740 --> 00:16:19.800 align:middle line:84%
literally raises it from
the dead, and then one day

00:16:19.800 --> 00:16:21.780 align:middle line:84%
is given the permission
to go off to Jerusalem,

00:16:21.780 --> 00:16:24.510 align:middle line:84%
meets a bunch of people
there that said, hey.

00:16:24.510 --> 00:16:26.560 align:middle line:84%
We come from the same
place in Central Europe.

00:16:26.560 --> 00:16:28.200 align:middle line:84%
Would you like to
create a new country?

00:16:28.200 --> 00:16:30.220 align:middle line:84%
And they said, hey,
that's a great idea.

00:16:30.220 --> 00:16:33.540 align:middle line:84%
We could start a whole
new real Christian place

00:16:33.540 --> 00:16:36.270 align:middle line:84%
of veneration, where the true
Christian brotherhood can

00:16:36.270 --> 00:16:37.260 align:middle line:90%
really develop itself.

00:16:37.260 --> 00:16:39.690 align:middle line:84%
And he said, well, we have
some friends, to which he

00:16:39.690 --> 00:16:42.030 align:middle line:90%
said, I have some friends, too.

00:16:42.030 --> 00:16:45.030 align:middle line:84%
And they were the people,
members of my family

00:16:45.030 --> 00:16:49.500 align:middle line:84%
called the De la Roche, were
actually members in Burgundy

00:16:49.500 --> 00:16:52.740 align:middle line:84%
who helped found the Cistercians
and the Templar Order.

00:16:52.740 --> 00:16:54.240 align:middle line:84%
So all of these
people from Burgundy

00:16:54.240 --> 00:16:56.670 align:middle line:84%
are now in Northern
Portugal, helping

00:16:56.670 --> 00:16:58.380 align:middle line:90%
to create this nation-kingdom.

00:16:58.380 --> 00:17:01.710 align:middle line:84%
And as he's clearing the
unwelcome Arabs from that land,

00:17:01.710 --> 00:17:04.119 align:middle line:84%
so the Templars are moving
in and helping him out.

00:17:04.119 --> 00:17:06.030 align:middle line:90%
This is a historical record.

00:17:06.030 --> 00:17:08.430 align:middle line:84%
It's on record saying
that knights actually

00:17:08.430 --> 00:17:11.490 align:middle line:84%
came back from Jerusalem
with Count Dom Henrique

00:17:11.490 --> 00:17:14.740 align:middle line:84%
to actually help him
create this relationship.

00:17:14.740 --> 00:17:19.410 align:middle line:84%
And by 1111, we actually see
that he gives them a castle.

00:17:19.410 --> 00:17:22.190 align:middle line:84%
So the Templars don't
exist yet, but yet they

00:17:22.190 --> 00:17:23.190 align:middle line:90%
are already in Portugal.

00:17:23.190 --> 00:17:26.069 align:middle line:84%
And they've been given a
castle and a piece of land.

00:17:26.069 --> 00:17:27.990 align:middle line:84%
Now that changes
the history totally

00:17:27.990 --> 00:17:29.580 align:middle line:84%
because it puts them
at the wrong time

00:17:29.580 --> 00:17:31.440 align:middle line:84%
and in the wrong place
in a different part

00:17:31.440 --> 00:17:34.380 align:middle line:84%
of the world, where they ought
not to be, but yet they are.

00:17:34.380 --> 00:17:37.230 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: OK, now this brings
us to a couple of things.

00:17:37.230 --> 00:17:40.560 align:middle line:84%
The town of Tomar, which is also
dedicated to Mary Magdalene,

00:17:40.560 --> 00:17:41.360 align:middle line:90%
right?

00:17:41.360 --> 00:17:42.160 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Oh, yes.

00:17:42.160 --> 00:17:45.190 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: They were teaching
the Templar values there, right?

00:17:45.190 --> 00:17:46.860 align:middle line:90%
But let's talk about--

00:17:46.860 --> 00:17:47.700 align:middle line:90%
the grail values.

00:17:47.700 --> 00:17:49.390 align:middle line:84%
I'm sorry, the
grail values there,

00:17:49.390 --> 00:17:51.450 align:middle line:84%
which we're going to start
getting into the grail in a bit

00:17:51.450 --> 00:17:53.491 align:middle line:84%
because this is really
where it's all leading to.

00:17:53.491 --> 00:17:54.291 align:middle line:90%


00:17:54.291 --> 00:17:55.440 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Yummy.

00:17:55.440 --> 00:17:57.480 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Let's talk
about the Cistercians

00:17:57.480 --> 00:17:59.790 align:middle line:84%
and what they were
offering society,

00:17:59.790 --> 00:18:01.800 align:middle line:84%
what they were
teaching, the knowledge

00:18:01.800 --> 00:18:04.770 align:middle line:84%
they had at that time as well,
and bring the story together

00:18:04.770 --> 00:18:06.200 align:middle line:90%
through those two lenses.

00:18:06.200 --> 00:18:08.570 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: Oh, they were
trying to recreate a utopia.

00:18:08.570 --> 00:18:10.500 align:middle line:84%
And it wasn't really
difficult in Europe,

00:18:10.500 --> 00:18:13.740 align:middle line:84%
where everything was basically
being ravaged to the ground.

00:18:13.740 --> 00:18:16.710 align:middle line:84%
And the church is pretty much
central to that ravaging.

00:18:16.710 --> 00:18:19.140 align:middle line:84%
So, of course, the
church was hated.

00:18:19.140 --> 00:18:21.180 align:middle line:90%
You know, they literally were.

00:18:21.180 --> 00:18:23.700 align:middle line:84%
And suddenly, the Cistercians
show up and say, hey.

00:18:23.700 --> 00:18:28.050 align:middle line:84%
We can actually show you how
to grow crops and tend animals.

00:18:28.050 --> 00:18:29.862 align:middle line:84%
We will help you
put schools together

00:18:29.862 --> 00:18:32.070 align:middle line:84%
to teach your children, so
that they understand right

00:18:32.070 --> 00:18:34.280 align:middle line:84%
from wrong and
understand information,

00:18:34.280 --> 00:18:37.134 align:middle line:84%
so that when you're fed
propaganda that is not

00:18:37.134 --> 00:18:39.300 align:middle line:84%
information, that's actually
someone else's opinion,

00:18:39.300 --> 00:18:41.200 align:middle line:90%
you can think for yourself.

00:18:41.200 --> 00:18:43.660 align:middle line:84%
And in order to do this,
we need your support.

00:18:43.660 --> 00:18:44.460 align:middle line:90%
We need land.

00:18:44.460 --> 00:18:45.793 align:middle line:90%
We need whatever money you have.

00:18:45.793 --> 00:18:47.940 align:middle line:84%
We'll put it into
escrow, and then we'll

00:18:47.940 --> 00:18:50.010 align:middle line:84%
put that money where
it needs to go.

00:18:50.010 --> 00:18:52.750 align:middle line:84%
When that group of people
raises itself from the dead,

00:18:52.750 --> 00:18:56.681 align:middle line:84%
literally, they can then give
us back a little bit in tithe.

00:18:56.681 --> 00:18:57.930 align:middle line:90%
We'll put it back into escrow.

00:18:57.930 --> 00:18:59.388 align:middle line:84%
We'll help another
group of people,

00:18:59.388 --> 00:19:01.010 align:middle line:90%
and together we grow outwards.

00:19:01.010 --> 00:19:01.810 align:middle line:90%
And they did.

00:19:01.810 --> 00:19:05.130 align:middle line:84%
They would settle in the most
inhospitable part of the land

00:19:05.130 --> 00:19:08.190 align:middle line:84%
and turn a desert into
a flourishing paradise,

00:19:08.190 --> 00:19:10.290 align:middle line:84%
literally within three
years, to the point where

00:19:10.290 --> 00:19:12.930 align:middle line:84%
they're selling surplus
food to the local villagers.

00:19:12.930 --> 00:19:14.850 align:middle line:90%
And that's how the word got out.

00:19:14.850 --> 00:19:18.350 align:middle line:84%
Someone here is not behaving
like those people in Rome.

00:19:18.350 --> 00:19:20.350 align:middle line:84%
These people are doing
something very different.

00:19:20.350 --> 00:19:20.850 align:middle line:90%
We like them.

00:19:20.850 --> 00:19:21.765 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And they were the
ones who would not be governed.

00:19:21.765 --> 00:19:22.545 align:middle line:90%


00:19:22.545 --> 00:19:23.160 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: And they
were the ones who

00:19:23.160 --> 00:19:24.701 align:middle line:84%
would not be governed,
because it was

00:19:24.701 --> 00:19:26.460 align:middle line:90%
about respect, mutual respect.

00:19:26.460 --> 00:19:27.540 align:middle line:90%
We give something.

00:19:27.540 --> 00:19:29.630 align:middle line:84%
You give it back, and
we all grow together.

00:19:29.630 --> 00:19:32.940 align:middle line:84%
And if we grow, you know,
in little pods, apart,

00:19:32.940 --> 00:19:33.740 align:middle line:90%
no one benefits.

00:19:33.740 --> 00:19:35.410 align:middle line:90%
You only benefit a few people.

00:19:35.410 --> 00:19:39.720 align:middle line:84%
We have to grow together so
that the whole society elevates

00:19:39.720 --> 00:19:41.650 align:middle line:90%
itself on an equal footing.

00:19:41.650 --> 00:19:44.460 align:middle line:84%
So it's a very utopian
paradise situation,

00:19:44.460 --> 00:19:46.950 align:middle line:84%
and it really began to work
in this little, tiny county

00:19:46.950 --> 00:19:48.720 align:middle line:84%
on the opposite side
of Europe, where

00:19:48.720 --> 00:19:51.737 align:middle line:84%
Rome had no idea what was going
on, because they were kept,

00:19:51.737 --> 00:19:53.820 align:middle line:84%
you know-- any time you
have any emissaries coming

00:19:53.820 --> 00:19:56.026 align:middle line:90%
from the pope, bye-bye.

00:19:56.026 --> 00:19:57.150 align:middle line:90%
We'll give you lip service.

00:19:57.150 --> 00:19:58.380 align:middle line:84%
We'll tell you that
we're all dirt poor.

00:19:58.380 --> 00:20:00.580 align:middle line:84%
We still believe in, you
know, the cross and Jesus

00:20:00.580 --> 00:20:01.080 align:middle line:90%
and all of that.

00:20:01.080 --> 00:20:03.413 align:middle line:84%
And in the meanwhile, we're
worshipping John the Baptist

00:20:03.413 --> 00:20:05.610 align:middle line:84%
and the pagan gods,
you know, which

00:20:05.610 --> 00:20:06.850 align:middle line:90%
are one and the same thing.

00:20:06.850 --> 00:20:09.570 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: So let's talk
about Dom Henrique's role

00:20:09.570 --> 00:20:12.110 align:middle line:84%
and then his progeny and
where it goes from there.

00:20:12.110 --> 00:20:12.910 align:middle line:90%


00:20:12.910 --> 00:20:15.110 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: So he meets
a very untimely death

00:20:15.110 --> 00:20:16.880 align:middle line:90%
around about 1114.

00:20:16.880 --> 00:20:20.060 align:middle line:84%
And this is where
suddenly the Templar plan

00:20:20.060 --> 00:20:22.220 align:middle line:84%
appears to have run
aground because they hadn't

00:20:22.220 --> 00:20:24.200 align:middle line:90%
counted on him dying so early.

00:20:24.200 --> 00:20:25.910 align:middle line:84%
And there's, like,
a breathing space

00:20:25.910 --> 00:20:29.000 align:middle line:84%
where nothing happens, at least
in terms of documentation.

00:20:29.000 --> 00:20:30.860 align:middle line:84%
We still have a
document in Jerusalem

00:20:30.860 --> 00:20:34.550 align:middle line:84%
where the Order of Sion is still
working with the Templars, who

00:20:34.550 --> 00:20:38.240 align:middle line:84%
are technically not yet the
Templars, but yet they are.

00:20:38.240 --> 00:20:41.000 align:middle line:84%
And they had to wait
until his son, who

00:20:41.000 --> 00:20:44.370 align:middle line:84%
was only nine years of age at
the time, Afonso Henrique--

00:20:44.370 --> 00:20:47.360 align:middle line:84%
they all had the same names
so it was very confusing.

00:20:47.360 --> 00:20:50.090 align:middle line:84%
He had to govern under
the rule of his mother

00:20:50.090 --> 00:20:53.120 align:middle line:84%
until he came of age around
the time of when he was 14

00:20:53.120 --> 00:20:55.310 align:middle line:84%
because kids had to grow
up very early in those days

00:20:55.310 --> 00:20:56.210 align:middle line:90%
in a time of warfare.

00:20:56.210 --> 00:20:58.850 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: His brother was
an interesting character

00:20:58.850 --> 00:20:59.660 align:middle line:90%
amidst this.

00:20:59.660 --> 00:21:01.493 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: Very interesting
character, indeed.

00:21:01.493 --> 00:21:03.950 align:middle line:84%
So in the meantime, they are
grooming this little kid,

00:21:03.950 --> 00:21:05.360 align:middle line:84%
who doesn't yet
realize that he's

00:21:05.360 --> 00:21:08.210 align:middle line:84%
going to become the first king
of this brand-new, independent

00:21:08.210 --> 00:21:10.010 align:middle line:90%
nation state called Portugal.

00:21:10.010 --> 00:21:12.500 align:middle line:10%
And assisting him
and the Templars

00:21:12.500 --> 00:21:16.580 align:middle line:10%
is also the head of the Knights
Hospitaller in Portugal, who

00:21:16.580 --> 00:21:20.640 align:middle line:10%
also groomed this young child
to be the future monarch, you

00:21:20.640 --> 00:21:22.640 align:middle line:10%
know, made sure that
this person was instilled

00:21:22.640 --> 00:21:24.490 align:middle line:10%
with the right
spiritual qualities.

00:21:24.490 --> 00:21:25.970 align:middle line:84%
And in the meantime,
it turns out

00:21:25.970 --> 00:21:28.340 align:middle line:84%
from another document
that was very rare

00:21:28.340 --> 00:21:31.310 align:middle line:84%
that the moment that
this young prince takes

00:21:31.310 --> 00:21:33.154 align:middle line:84%
his side next to his
mother-- and still he

00:21:33.154 --> 00:21:34.070 align:middle line:90%
is not able to govern.

00:21:34.070 --> 00:21:37.470 align:middle line:84%
His mother is writing
all the documents.

00:21:37.470 --> 00:21:39.230 align:middle line:84%
Bernard of Clairvaux
sends a group

00:21:39.230 --> 00:21:41.570 align:middle line:84%
of monks over to
Portugal, including

00:21:41.570 --> 00:21:44.510 align:middle line:84%
one of the original Knights
Templar, Brother Roland--

00:21:44.510 --> 00:21:46.550 align:middle line:84%
