Cistercian all along--

00:21:46.550 --> 00:21:50.200 align:middle line:84%
to ask the young
Prince Afonso, oh,

00:21:50.200 --> 00:21:53.550 align:middle line:84%
do you mind if we build the
first Cistercian monastery here

00:21:53.550 --> 00:21:54.590 align:middle line:90%
in your county?

00:21:54.590 --> 00:21:58.490 align:middle line:84%
And he said, absolutely, because
basically what was happening

00:21:58.490 --> 00:22:01.610 align:middle line:84%
is that young Afonso was
granting his uncle, Bernard

00:22:01.610 --> 00:22:05.510 align:middle line:84%
of Clairvaux, permission
to set up shop in Portugal.

00:22:05.510 --> 00:22:08.840 align:middle line:84%
Now we're beginning to see how
the whole story begins to play

00:22:08.840 --> 00:22:11.030 align:middle line:90%
itself out through family ties.

00:22:11.030 --> 00:22:15.800 align:middle line:84%
Bernard of Clairvaux already
had a member of his family ready

00:22:15.800 --> 00:22:18.260 align:middle line:84%
and propped up to go on
the throne of Portugal that

00:22:18.260 --> 00:22:21.740 align:middle line:84%
was aided by the Templars, who
were essentially his monks.

00:22:21.740 --> 00:22:25.610 align:middle line:84%
So the whole thing is one big,
very tightly committed family,

00:22:25.610 --> 00:22:28.070 align:middle line:84%
very patient, the plan
that was taking place here.

00:22:28.070 --> 00:22:31.100 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, he
