protect the bloodline of David.

00:24:03.480 --> 00:24:06.200 align:middle line:84%
Now why would you put that as
a line item in a swearing-in

00:24:06.200 --> 00:24:07.880 align:middle line:84%
ceremony unless
there is a bloodline

00:24:07.880 --> 00:24:09.740 align:middle line:90%
to protect in Portugal?

00:24:09.740 --> 00:24:11.900 align:middle line:84%
And that's where
suddenly I realized

00:24:11.900 --> 00:24:15.230 align:middle line:84%
my nose has gotten too close to
the honeypot because I thought,

00:24:15.230 --> 00:24:16.610 align:middle line:90%
let me just ask a few questions.

00:24:16.610 --> 00:24:18.780 align:middle line:84%
And, bang, the door
starts slamming.

00:24:18.780 --> 00:24:22.760 align:middle line:84%
So I'm very good friends
with a high-level Freemason

00:24:22.760 --> 00:24:26.630 align:middle line:84%
here in America,
a lady, actually,

00:24:26.630 --> 00:24:29.750 align:middle line:84%
part of the Scottish
Rite movement,

00:24:29.750 --> 00:24:32.100 align:middle line:84%
because they allow
women into the movement.

00:24:32.100 --> 00:24:35.780 align:middle line:84%
And she said, well, I could
ask for that on your behalf

00:24:35.780 --> 00:24:38.810 align:middle line:84%
when I go off to Belgium
to our yearly conclave.

00:24:38.810 --> 00:24:40.650 align:middle line:84%
She comes back, and
I said, is there

00:24:40.650 --> 00:24:41.983 align:middle line:90%
anything you could help me with?

00:24:41.983 --> 00:24:43.910 align:middle line:84%
And she says, well,
I was just told,

00:24:43.910 --> 00:24:47.930 align:middle line:84%
quite firmly and politely,
just ask your friend to desist

00:24:47.930 --> 00:24:49.610 align:middle line:90%
from pursuing this any further.

00:24:49.610 --> 00:24:50.230 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: There's your answer.

00:24:50.230 --> 00:24:52.010 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: I thought, that tells
me exactly what I need to know.

00:24:52.010 --> 00:24:52.880 align:middle line:90%
Thank you very much.

00:24:52.880 --> 00:24:53.030 align:middle line:90%


00:24:53.030 --> 00:24:55.430 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: OK, so it's
quite possible that was

00:24:55.430 --> 00:24:56.604 align:middle line:90%
part of that bloodline.

00:24:56.604 --> 00:24:58.145 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: Yes, and
I think that's also

00:24:58.145 --> 00:25:00.380 align:middle line:84%
another reason why they
wanted a tract of land

00:25:00.380 --> 00:25:02.880 align:middle line:84%
as far from Rome
meddling in their affairs

00:25:02.880 --> 00:25:05.337 align:middle line:84%
as possible, because as
we know, if the Templars--

00:25:05.337 --> 00:25:07.670 align:middle line:84%
and we know this from the
fact that a lot of the Templar

00:25:07.670 --> 00:25:10.220 align:middle line:84%
Knights were part of
the Order of Sion.

00:25:10.220 --> 00:25:12.380 align:middle line:84%
And the Order of
Sion's declared aim

00:25:12.380 --> 00:25:15.780 align:middle line:84%
was to bring back the bloodline
through the Merovingians that

00:25:15.780 --> 00:25:18.390 align:middle line:84%
went back to Jerusalem,
that went back to Sumeria.

00:25:18.390 --> 00:25:19.970 align:middle line:84%
Then, yes, that
makes a lot of sense.

00:25:19.970 --> 00:25:23.700 align:middle line:84%
Put them as far away from the
grasp of the pope as possible.

00:25:23.700 --> 00:25:25.495 align:middle line:84%
They may even still
be around today.

00:25:25.495 --> 00:25:27.120 align:middle line:84%
Hell, I could be part
of the bloodline.

00:25:27.120 --> 00:25:27.370 align:middle line:90%
Who knows?

00:25:27.370 --> 00:25:28.280 align:middle line:90%
Maybe I have land somewhere.

00:25:28.280 --> 00:25:28.670 align:middle line:90%
Who knows?

00:25:28.670 --> 00:25:29.070 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, that's
what I'm saying.

00:25:29.070 --> 00:25:30.230 align:middle line:90%
No, I have no doubt.

00:25:30.230 --> 00:25:31.500 align:middle line:90%
Good luck getting the deed.

00:25:31.500 --> 00:25:33.535 align:middle line:84%
But nonetheless,
I'm sure you do.

00:25:33.535 --> 00:25:35.160 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: But it is
a fascinating story.

00:25:35.160 --> 00:25:40.500 align:middle line:84%
And, in fact, his brother,
Afonso's brother, the prince,

00:25:40.500 --> 00:25:43.980 align:middle line:84%
he turns out to have started
a branch of the Templars

00:25:43.980 --> 00:25:47.070 align:middle line:84%
which hardly anyone talks
about called the House of Avis

00:25:47.070 --> 00:25:48.090 align:middle line:90%
in Portugal.

00:25:48.090 --> 00:25:51.959 align:middle line:10%
And their logo is the Templar
logo with the fleur-de-lis.

00:25:51.959 --> 00:25:54.250 align:middle line:10%
And you've got to look at
these symbols very carefully.

00:25:54.250 --> 00:25:57.080 align:middle line:10%
There's a lot of crosses,
which people say, oh, these

00:25:57.080 --> 00:25:57.880 align:middle line:10%
are all Templars.

00:25:57.880 --> 00:25:59.500 align:middle line:10%
Well, no, they are
different branches,

00:25:59.500 --> 00:26:01.630 align:middle line:10%
and they all do very
different things.

00:26:01.630 --> 00:26:04.400 align:middle line:10%
But if you look at the logo of
the House of Avis in Portugal,

00:26:04.400 --> 00:26:07.020 align:middle line:10%
it is the Templar logo mixed
with the fleur-de-lis, which,

00:26:07.020 --> 00:26:09.720 align:middle line:10%
of course, is the symbol of
the Merovingian bloodline

00:26:09.720 --> 00:26:11.131 align:middle line:10%
in France.

00:26:11.131 --> 00:26:12.630 align:middle line:84%
I'm just going to
put that out there

00:26:12.630 --> 00:26:15.650 align:middle line:84%
because anybody feels compelled
to pursue that further.

00:26:15.650 --> 00:26:17.430 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: How about you?

00:26:17.430 --> 00:26:20.044 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: If there's a
crowd-funded source that

00:26:20.044 --> 00:26:22.210 align:middle line:84%
will help me do that, I
would love to get into this.

00:26:22.210 --> 00:26:23.300 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You'll get
crowd funding, Freddy.

00:26:23.300 --> 00:26:24.540 align:middle line:90%
Go for it.

00:26:24.540 --> 00:26:26.910 align:middle line:84%
OK, now, on these lands
also, interestingly,

00:26:26.910 --> 00:26:30.900 align:middle line:84%
is a temple devoted
to Isis, right?

00:26:30.900 --> 00:26:32.910 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: Yes, wherever
they went in Portugal--

00:26:32.910 --> 00:26:34.326 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And
there's a connection

00:26:34.326 --> 00:26:37.730 align:middle line:84%
between Mary Magdalene and Isis
in some schools of thought.

00:26:37.730 --> 00:26:41.530 align:middle line:84%
But Isis is misunderstood
in itself, anyway.

00:26:41.530 --> 00:26:44.520 align:middle line:84%
But nonetheless, still,
there's a temple to Isis.

00:26:44.520 --> 00:26:46.700 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: Yes, and
they're everywhere.

00:26:46.700 --> 00:26:48.760 align:middle line:84%
In fact, wherever the
Templars went around,

00:26:48.760 --> 00:26:51.780 align:middle line:84%
and specifically in Portugal
and other parts of Europe,

00:26:51.780 --> 00:26:53.900 align:middle line:84%
wherever they
founded their temples

00:26:53.900 --> 00:26:56.400 align:middle line:84%
or they went to
actually retrieve

00:26:56.400 --> 00:26:58.800 align:middle line:84%
certain places on the
land or rebuild them,

00:26:58.800 --> 00:27:01.926 align:middle line:84%
they were always original
temples, dedicated to Isis.

00:27:01.926 --> 00:27:04.050 align:middle line:84%
So if you follow the story
line all the way back as

00:27:04.050 --> 00:27:07.670 align:middle line:84%
far as it will go to
Egypt and also to Sumeria,

00:27:07.670 --> 00:27:08.650 align:middle line:90%
why is this important?

00:27:08.650 --> 00:27:10.150 align:middle line:90%
Why is this important?

00:27:10.150 --> 00:27:12.390 align:middle line:84%
Why is Isis so important
in their understanding?

00:27:12.390 --> 00:27:14.790 align:middle line:84%
Well, in the beginning,
it turns out,

00:27:14.790 --> 00:27:17.460 align:middle line:84%
the most remotest of
cultures talk about the fact

00:27:17.460 --> 00:27:20.550 align:middle line:84%
that in the beginning
of all creation,

00:27:20.550 --> 00:27:24.660 align:middle line:84%
the world, the universe, was
created from a wonderful--

00:27:24.660 --> 00:27:28.290 align:middle line:84%
not an explosion, but just
an outpouring of energy.

00:27:28.290 --> 00:27:33.270 align:middle line:84%
And the source of this energy,
because it's, you know,

00:27:33.270 --> 00:27:36.720 align:middle line:84%
creative, it has to
be a feminine quality.

00:27:36.720 --> 00:27:39.210 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: We're on the same
page, prima materia itself.

00:27:39.210 --> 00:27:42.127 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: So it's not a guy with
a white that runs the universe.

00:27:42.127 --> 00:27:42.960 align:middle line:10%
And it's not really.

00:27:42.960 --> 00:27:43.760 align:middle line:10%
It's an it.

00:27:43.760 --> 00:27:45.870 align:middle line:10%
But the ancestors looked
at this and said, well,

00:27:45.870 --> 00:27:49.020 align:middle line:10%
if it's a creative
and outstanding force,

00:27:49.020 --> 00:27:50.910 align:middle line:10%
then that would be
a feminine quality.

00:27:50.910 --> 00:27:55.320 align:middle line:84%
And because in the beginning
the universe was a dark place,

00:27:55.320 --> 00:27:57.390 align:middle line:84%
because then there was
light and there was sound,

00:27:57.390 --> 00:28:00.140 align:middle line:84%
so before that, there had to
be darkness in the universe.

00:28:00.140 --> 00:28:02.010 align:middle line:84%
But because the
universe was created,

00:28:02.010 --> 00:28:05.220 align:middle line:84%
therefore all the wisdom and
knowledge of the universe

00:28:05.220 --> 00:28:07.530 align:middle line:90%
had to be contained in the dark.

00:28:07.530 --> 00:28:10.420 align:middle line:84%
And that's where they got the
concept of the divine virgin

00:28:10.420 --> 00:28:13.130 align:middle line:84%
that wears a black skin,
or the black Madonna,

00:28:13.130 --> 00:28:14.996 align:middle line:84%
as it became known
in Central Europe.

00:28:14.996 --> 00:28:15.870 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Great void.

00:28:15.870 --> 00:28:18.380 align:middle line:10%
>>SILVA: Who is basically
an interpretation of Isis,

00:28:18.380 --> 00:28:22.260 align:middle line:10%
who represents this ideal of
the embodiment of all knowledge

00:28:22.260 --> 00:28:24.100 align:middle line:10%
in the universe, whose
husband, of course,

00:28:24.100 --> 00:28:27.087 align:middle line:10%
is a resurrected hero who
goes into the other world

00:28:27.087 --> 00:28:29.170 align:middle line:10%
on December the 21st, comes
back three days later.

00:28:29.170 --> 00:28:30.420 align:middle line:90%
He rises from the dead.

00:28:30.420 --> 00:28:31.920 align:middle line:84%
So that's what the
Templars were following.

00:28:31.920 --> 00:28:34.336 align:middle line:84%
And it's very important to
know because Mary Magdalene was

00:28:34.336 --> 00:28:35.869 align:middle line:90%
part of that lineage.

00:28:35.869 --> 00:28:38.160 align:middle line:84%
That's why they were supportive
of her and nobody else.

00:28:38.160 --> 00:28:41.010 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Exactly, and that
was ancient, ancient, ancient

00:28:41.010 --> 00:28:43.140 align:middle line:84%
Atlantean knowledge,
the understanding

00:28:43.140 --> 00:28:48.127 align:middle line:84%
of simply the creation of
all, and thus, Isis, Isis.

00:28:48.127 --> 00:28:50.460 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: And it's amazing
that they kept the story going

00:28:50.460 --> 00:28:52.380 align:middle line:84%
through different groups
of people for, what,

00:28:52.380 --> 00:28:54.595 align:middle line:90%
11,000 years, at least?

00:28:54.595 --> 00:28:55.470 align:middle line:90%
That's extraordinary.

00:28:55.470 --> 00:28:57.750 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: At least, at
least, yes, OK, so that's

00:28:57.750 --> 00:28:59.130 align:middle line:90%
the part I wanted to get into.

00:28:59.130 --> 00:29:01.290 align:middle line:90%
So you've gone there.

00:29:01.290 --> 00:29:04.590 align:middle line:84%
One of the things that's kind
of a manifestation of this

00:29:04.590 --> 00:29:09.390 align:middle line:84%
that I found so beautiful
in your book, it was Afonso.

00:29:09.390 --> 00:29:11.780 align:middle line:84%
His uncle was Bernard
de Clairvaux, right?

00:29:11.780 --> 00:29:12.690 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Yeah.

00:29:12.690 --> 00:29:17.070 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And he
dedicated an incredible--

00:29:17.070 --> 00:29:18.330 align:middle line:90%
it's not a cathedral.

00:29:18.330 --> 00:29:19.710 align:middle line:90%
Is it a chapel, a cathedral?

00:29:19.710 --> 00:29:22.140 align:middle line:84%
What would you call it,
this incredible edifice?

00:29:22.140 --> 00:29:23.384 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: In Tomar?

00:29:23.384 --> 00:29:24.330 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Yeah.

00:29:24.330 --> 00:29:26.520 align:middle line:10%
>>SILVA: Oh, it's a round--

00:29:26.520 --> 00:29:29.250 align:middle line:10%
they call it a church,
the round church,

00:29:29.250 --> 00:29:31.877 align:middle line:10%
except for there's a bit
of a problem with this.

00:29:31.877 --> 00:29:32.960 align:middle line:10%
And it's inside a citadel.

00:29:32.960 --> 00:29:35.250 align:middle line:10%
It's inside a castle, of
course, because, you know,

00:29:35.250 --> 00:29:38.490 align:middle line:10%
the Saracens were
after the land.

00:29:38.490 --> 00:29:41.850 align:middle line:84%
So they basically settled in
this place called Tomar, which

00:29:41.850 --> 00:29:44.060 align:middle line:90%
literally means a palm tree.

00:29:44.060 --> 00:29:46.336 align:middle line:84%
And I was looking at the
Weather Channel back then.

00:29:46.336 --> 00:29:48.710 align:middle line:84%
And apparently, it was too
cold to grow palm trees there.

00:29:48.710 --> 00:29:50.293 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, well,
now why would you

00:29:50.293 --> 00:29:53.610 align:middle line:84%
name a town after a plant that
doesn't grow in this location?

00:29:53.610 --> 00:29:55.000 align:middle line:90%
That doesn't make any sense.

00:29:55.000 --> 00:29:58.200 align:middle line:84%
They would always name
things after local features.

00:29:58.200 --> 00:30:00.570 align:middle line:84%
And it turns out
that Tomar literally

00:30:00.570 --> 00:30:02.370 align:middle line:84%
is a corruption of
Tomara, which is

00:30:02.370 --> 00:30:04.110 align:middle line:84%
the original name
of the town, which

00:30:04.110 --> 00:30:07.260 align:middle line:84%
happens to be one of the
daughters of Mary Magdalene.

00:30:07.260 --> 00:30:09.010 align:middle line:84%
And that's where the
penny begins to drop.

00:30:09.010 --> 00:30:11.670 align:middle line:84%
And I went, holy mother,
this is extraordinary.

00:30:11.670 --> 00:30:12.740 align:middle line:90%
Maybe it's a coincidence.

00:30:12.740 --> 00:30:16.950 align:middle line:84%
Well, they built the most famous
of their buildings, this round

00:30:16.950 --> 00:30:19.740 align:middle line:84%
tower, except it was
never used as a church.

00:30:19.740 --> 00:30:21.600 align:middle line:84%
They used a church
outside the citadel

00:30:21.600 --> 00:30:22.817 align:middle line:90%
for their daily activities.

00:30:22.817 --> 00:30:24.900 align:middle line:84%
Why would you need two
churches within half a mile

00:30:24.900 --> 00:30:25.980 align:middle line:90%
of each other?

00:30:25.980 --> 00:30:27.700 align:middle line:90%
Then it got even weirder.

00:30:27.700 --> 00:30:29.610 align:middle line:90%
The tower never had a door.

00:30:29.610 --> 00:30:31.590 align:middle line:90%
So how would you get in?

00:30:31.590 --> 00:30:35.010 align:middle line:84%
It turns out the Templars used
to go through a secret tunnel

00:30:35.010 --> 00:30:38.100 align:middle line:84%
and come out through
the actual floor, just

00:30:38.100 --> 00:30:41.940 align:middle line:84%
exactly like the Essenes
used to do on Temple Mount

00:30:41.940 --> 00:30:45.360 align:middle line:84%
because they had a secret
entrance that they had to reach

00:30:45.360 --> 00:30:49.740 align:middle line:84%
via a secret chamber that
they had to pull part

00:30:49.740 --> 00:30:53.040 align:middle line:84%
of the floor that had a ring
on it, through which they

00:30:53.040 --> 00:30:55.931 align:middle line:84%
descended to do their
private and very most

00:30:55.931 --> 00:30:57.680 align:middle line:84%
secret of ceremonies,
which is the raising

00:30:57.680 --> 00:31:00.150 align:middle line:84%
the dead ceremonies, a
very misunderstood concept,

00:31:00.150 --> 00:31:01.260 align:middle line:90%
by the way.

00:31:01.260 --> 00:31:04.210 align:middle line:84%
This is the central tenet of the
third degree of Scottish Rite

00:31:04.210 --> 00:31:05.010 align:middle line:90%
Freemasonry.

00:31:05.010 --> 00:31:06.360 align:middle line:90%
So it survives.

00:31:06.360 --> 00:31:09.690 align:middle line:84%
So because the Scottish Rite
Freemasonry is essentially

00:31:09.690 --> 00:31:11.685 align:middle line:84%
the renamed Templars
in Scotland,

00:31:11.685 --> 00:31:13.560 align:middle line:84%
we now know that the
Templars were practicing

00:31:13.560 --> 00:31:14.880 align:middle line:90%
the same thing in Tomar.

00:31:14.880 --> 00:31:16.980 align:middle line:84%
And they built a
mirror image of what

00:31:16.980 --> 00:31:19.870 align:middle line:84%
was happening on
Mount Zion and also

00:31:19.870 --> 00:31:21.900 align:middle line:84%
on the Temple Mount
in Tomar in Portugal.

00:31:21.900 --> 00:31:22.890 align:middle line:90%
And it's still there.

00:31:22.890 --> 00:31:26.250 align:middle line:84%
The vestiges of the actual
secret chamber are still there.

00:31:26.250 --> 00:31:29.280 align:middle line:84%
I found this in a local library,
in a newspaper account that

00:31:29.280 --> 00:31:32.130 align:middle line:84%
talked about the
local people in 1940,

00:31:32.130 --> 00:31:35.049 align:middle line:84%
the craftsman, saying, well,
we had to shore up the building

00:31:35.049 --> 00:31:36.090 align:middle line:90%
because it was crumbling.

00:31:36.090 --> 00:31:40.560 align:middle line:84%
We had to put sort of a gird
of concrete around the base.

00:31:40.560 --> 00:31:42.720 align:middle line:84%
And unfortunately,
we had to hide

00:31:42.720 --> 00:31:45.030 align:middle line:84%
a door which was the
entrance, the second entrance,

00:31:45.030 --> 00:31:47.580 align:middle line:84%
to a secret crypt,
where the knights used

00:31:47.580 --> 00:31:50.444 align:middle line:84%
to conduct their most secret
and sacred of ceremonies.

00:31:50.444 --> 00:31:52.110 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And that's
where we're headed.

00:31:52.110 --> 00:31:55.232 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: Exactly, for the inner
brotherhood of the Templars,

00:31:55.232 --> 00:31:56.190 align:middle line:90%
because there were two.

00:31:56.190 --> 00:31:57.940 align:middle line:84%
There's the outer
brotherhood, and there's

00:31:57.940 --> 00:31:58.980 align:middle line:90%
the inner brotherhood.

00:31:58.980 --> 00:32:00.630 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Alcobaka.

00:32:00.630 --> 00:32:01.520 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Alcobaca.

00:32:01.520 --> 00:32:02.320 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Baca.

00:32:02.320 --> 00:32:05.400 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: Oh, yes, oh,
that's a beautiful place.

00:32:05.400 --> 00:32:07.350 align:middle line:10%
If you ever want to
travel anywhere in Europe

00:32:07.350 --> 00:32:11.130 align:middle line:10%
and see the true Gothic at
its most pure, where there's

00:32:11.130 --> 00:32:15.210 align:middle line:10%
no adornment, and see the actual
vision of Bernard of Clairvaux

00:32:15.210 --> 00:32:17.730 align:middle line:10%
in stone, the
monastery of Alcobaca.

00:32:17.730 --> 00:32:19.860 align:middle line:90%
I take people there on tour.

00:32:19.860 --> 00:32:22.597 align:middle line:84%
And usually, I talk a lot
when, obviously, I go on tour

00:32:22.597 --> 00:32:23.430 align:middle line:90%
and describe things.

00:32:23.430 --> 00:32:24.480 align:middle line:90%
I didn't say a word.

00:32:24.480 --> 00:32:26.730 align:middle line:84%
And people were saying, are
you going to say something

00:32:26.730 --> 00:32:29.124 align:middle line:90%
