absolutely true.

00:36:45.350 --> 00:36:49.080 align:middle line:84%
The Essenes, like the Templars,
believed in abstinence

00:36:49.080 --> 00:36:52.410 align:middle line:84%
for the sake of performing the
rites with their single partner

00:36:52.410 --> 00:36:54.870 align:middle line:84%
and holding all of
their money in escrow.

00:36:54.870 --> 00:36:57.220 align:middle line:84%
So then they could use
it for the greater good.

00:36:57.220 --> 00:36:58.801 align:middle line:84%
That's what it was
really all about.

00:36:58.801 --> 00:37:00.300 align:middle line:84%
So the Essenes had
two brotherhoods,

00:37:00.300 --> 00:37:01.590 align:middle line:90%
like the Templars.

00:37:01.590 --> 00:37:03.120 align:middle line:84%
They believed in
life after death.

00:37:03.120 --> 00:37:08.340 align:middle line:84%
They believed in ritual
bathing as a first act

00:37:08.340 --> 00:37:11.250 align:middle line:84%
towards the path of
initiation, which literally

00:37:11.250 --> 00:37:13.350 align:middle line:90%
means to become conscious.

00:37:13.350 --> 00:37:15.000 align:middle line:90%
That's what initiation means.

00:37:15.000 --> 00:37:17.640 align:middle line:84%
The Templars practiced
exactly the same ritual.

00:37:17.640 --> 00:37:19.920 align:middle line:84%
And there was a five-step
process, the end of which

00:37:19.920 --> 00:37:25.050 align:middle line:84%
was going into a secret chamber
under your main sacred building

00:37:25.050 --> 00:37:27.420 align:middle line:90%
where you took a narcotic.

00:37:27.420 --> 00:37:31.540 align:middle line:84%
And you then declared a vow to
discover the joys of paradise,

00:37:31.540 --> 00:37:34.890 align:middle line:84%
which is what the Templar
initiates, joining the order,

00:37:34.890 --> 00:37:36.420 align:middle line:90%
also declared the same vow.

00:37:36.420 --> 00:37:39.961 align:middle line:84%
We join the Templar Order to
discover the joys of paradise.

00:37:39.961 --> 00:37:41.460 align:middle line:84%
Doesn't sound like
the kind of thing

00:37:41.460 --> 00:37:45.960 align:middle line:84%
that a knight would declare
to go off and fight.

00:37:45.960 --> 00:37:50.190 align:middle line:84%
People just don't do that
if they're into fighting.

00:37:50.190 --> 00:37:52.019 align:middle line:84%
So they practiced
this thing called

00:37:52.019 --> 00:37:54.310 align:middle line:84%
the living resurrection,
where the person was taken out

00:37:54.310 --> 00:37:54.780 align:middle line:90%
of body.

00:37:54.780 --> 00:37:56.488 align:middle line:84%
When they came back
into the living body,

00:37:56.488 --> 00:37:58.500 align:middle line:84%
they are declared
risen from the dead.

00:37:58.500 --> 00:38:00.410 align:middle line:84%
And the Templars
practiced the same thing,

00:38:00.410 --> 00:38:03.550 align:middle line:84%
and the Freemasons that followed
did exactly the same thing.

00:38:03.550 --> 00:38:06.530 align:middle line:84%
So the Essenes were essentially
following a very old tradition

00:38:06.530 --> 00:38:07.530 align:middle line:90%
by their time.

00:38:07.530 --> 00:38:09.360 align:middle line:84%
And 1,000 years
later, the Templars

00:38:09.360 --> 00:38:11.750 align:middle line:84%
pick up on it, right
down to the white robes.

00:38:11.750 --> 00:38:13.810 align:middle line:84%
The Cistercians, to
a certain degree,

00:38:13.810 --> 00:38:15.660 align:middle line:90%
did exactly the same thing.

00:38:15.660 --> 00:38:18.600 align:middle line:84%
And the Scottish Rite Masons
followed on from that as well.

00:38:18.600 --> 00:38:21.630 align:middle line:84%
So it's a continuation of a
very long tradition, borrowing

00:38:21.630 --> 00:38:23.690 align:middle line:84%
from the same book,
which I believe

00:38:23.690 --> 00:38:25.440 align:middle line:84%
is the Book of John
the Baptist, which

00:38:25.440 --> 00:38:27.600 align:middle line:84%
the Mandaeans to this
very day, are still

00:38:27.600 --> 00:38:29.550 align:middle line:90%
practicing in Southern Iraq.

00:38:29.550 --> 00:38:30.870 align:middle line:90%
Now here's the irony.

00:38:30.870 --> 00:38:34.380 align:middle line:84%
The Mandaeans, who read
from the Book of John, which

00:38:34.380 --> 00:38:36.420 align:middle line:84%
