00:40:57.634 --> 00:40:59.800 align:middle line:84%
But if you put this in the
hands of the wrong people

00:40:59.800 --> 00:41:01.307 align:middle line:84%
with the wrong
spiritual ideal, you

00:41:01.307 --> 00:41:02.890 align:middle line:84%
can use that same
energy, that doesn't

00:41:02.890 --> 00:41:05.200 align:middle line:84%
know right or wrong,
into the wrong hands.

00:41:05.200 --> 00:41:07.780 align:middle line:84%
And they can use it to
control populations.

00:41:07.780 --> 00:41:09.610 align:middle line:90%
That's why they kept it secret.

00:41:09.610 --> 00:41:11.840 align:middle line:84%
And then through
the Order of Sion

00:41:11.840 --> 00:41:14.080 align:middle line:84%
that said that we've
got this mandate that

00:41:14.080 --> 00:41:17.260 align:middle line:84%
goes all the way back, so when
the monks calling themselves

00:41:17.260 --> 00:41:21.880 align:middle line:84%
the Order of Sion show up
in I think it was about 1060

00:41:21.880 --> 00:41:24.340 align:middle line:84%
in Northern Europe,
declaring themselves

00:41:24.340 --> 00:41:28.570 align:middle line:84%
to be the Order of Sion,
that are basically picking up

00:41:28.570 --> 00:41:30.520 align:middle line:84%
a thread that's 1,000
years old, now we

00:41:30.520 --> 00:41:31.870 align:middle line:84%
know they're telling
the truth, because you

00:41:31.870 --> 00:41:32.911 align:middle line:90%
can't make this stuff up.

00:41:32.911 --> 00:41:34.240 align:middle line:90%
It's too convoluted.

00:41:34.240 --> 00:41:35.740 align:middle line:90%
The story is so complex.

00:41:35.740 --> 00:41:37.399 align:middle line:84%
Why would you make
this stuff up?

00:41:37.399 --> 00:41:39.190 align:middle line:84%
And they are saying
that we have maintained

00:41:39.190 --> 00:41:41.470 align:middle line:84%
this tradition, this
hidden tradition

00:41:41.470 --> 00:41:45.040 align:middle line:84%
of the spiritual essence,
that now is the time

00:41:45.040 --> 00:41:48.640 align:middle line:84%
to pick up on that because
there's a group of people that

00:41:48.640 --> 00:41:51.640 align:middle line:84%
are desperate enough to go and
fight all the way across Europe

00:41:51.640 --> 00:41:52.790 align:middle line:90%
and liberate Jerusalem.

00:41:52.790 --> 00:41:55.210 align:middle line:84%
This is our window to
recapture those books,

00:41:55.210 --> 00:41:58.090 align:middle line:84%
bring them back to Europe,
and create a new nation-state,

00:41:58.090 --> 00:42:00.880 align:middle line:84%
and rebuild this
true Christianity.

00:42:00.880 --> 00:42:04.120 align:middle line:84%
It's a wonderful romantic story,
and complicated and difficult.

00:42:04.120 --> 00:42:05.494 align:middle line:90%
But they stuck to it.

00:42:05.494 --> 00:42:06.910 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: You
touched on something

00:42:06.910 --> 00:42:10.950 align:middle line:84%
a moment ago about, again,
this constant fight,

00:42:10.950 --> 00:42:12.910 align:middle line:84%
a struggle between
light and dark,

00:42:12.910 --> 00:42:16.090 align:middle line:84%
between trying to preserve
this valuable knowledge so that

00:42:16.090 --> 00:42:17.290 align:middle line:90%
isn't misused.

00:42:17.290 --> 00:42:21.880 align:middle line:84%
And as we talked about earlier,
and I included you in it,

00:42:21.880 --> 00:42:24.760 align:middle line:84%
that we have entities
that continue incarnating

00:42:24.760 --> 00:42:27.640 align:middle line:84%
throughout history to
bring back knowledge,

00:42:27.640 --> 00:42:30.430 align:middle line:84%
to bring back true tenets
of universal understanding

00:42:30.430 --> 00:42:34.270 align:middle line:84%
and light to the population,
or those with ears to hear,

00:42:34.270 --> 00:42:35.860 align:middle line:90%
so to speak.

00:42:35.860 --> 00:42:38.800 align:middle line:84%
We have to remember,
the exact same thing

00:42:38.800 --> 00:42:40.450 align:middle line:90%
exists on the other side.

00:42:40.450 --> 00:42:43.060 align:middle line:84%
We live on a planet
that is suspended

00:42:43.060 --> 00:42:44.780 align:middle line:90%
between light and dark.

00:42:44.780 --> 00:42:47.050 align:middle line:84%
That's what makes it so
intriguing here, right?

00:42:47.050 --> 00:42:48.220 align:middle line:90%
We can choose our path.

00:42:48.220 --> 00:42:49.450 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: It's like a big,
experimental way station.

00:42:49.450 --> 00:42:51.550 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Exactly,
so I would have

00:42:51.550 --> 00:42:54.910 align:middle line:84%
to assume that you have the
mirror image of those who

00:42:54.910 --> 00:42:58.660 align:middle line:84%
are doing it, bringing
the knowledge forth again

00:42:58.660 --> 00:43:01.690 align:middle line:84%
and again throughout history
at certain key windows, which

00:43:01.690 --> 00:43:03.460 align:middle line:90%
may be astrologically aligned.

00:43:03.460 --> 00:43:04.690 align:middle line:90%
I don't know.

00:43:04.690 --> 00:43:07.040 align:middle line:90%
There's some thought on that.

00:43:07.040 --> 00:43:09.400 align:middle line:84%
You also have the key
forces of dark coming back

00:43:09.400 --> 00:43:12.657 align:middle line:84%
at the same time to
attempt to counter it.

00:43:12.657 --> 00:43:14.740 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: And, of course,
the great symbol for that

00:43:14.740 --> 00:43:17.350 align:middle line:84%
is the checkerboard
pattern that was adopted

00:43:17.350 --> 00:43:20.860 align:middle line:84%
by the early Templars and
also by the Masonic Order

00:43:20.860 --> 00:43:23.650 align:middle line:84%
because it's not really about
being very, very lighty,

00:43:23.650 --> 00:43:26.710 align:middle line:84%
because when you get to lighty,
you lose track of the fact

00:43:26.710 --> 00:43:29.650 align:middle line:84%
that there's a big darkness here
that you have to be aware of.

00:43:29.650 --> 00:43:32.080 align:middle line:84%
The idea is to look at
both sides of the equation,

00:43:32.080 --> 00:43:34.750 align:middle line:84%
kind of like Star
Wars, really, you know,

00:43:34.750 --> 00:43:36.690 align:middle line:84%
which is a great example
in this day and age.

00:43:36.690 --> 00:43:38.280 align:middle line:84%
It's the rewriting
of the Grail myth,

00:43:38.280 --> 00:43:41.200 align:middle line:84%
essentially, where,
you know, Anakin

00:43:41.200 --> 00:43:44.110 align:middle line:84%
is a Jedi, which is
actually an Egyptian name

00:43:44.110 --> 00:43:47.120 align:middle line:84%
for the pillar of the universe,
by the way, the Djed pillar.

00:43:47.120 --> 00:43:48.620 align:middle line:84%
And he starts off
being very lighty.

00:43:48.620 --> 00:43:50.077 align:middle line:84%
He gets seduced
by the dark side,

00:43:50.077 --> 00:43:51.160 align:middle line:90%
develops an understanding.

00:43:51.160 --> 00:43:54.580 align:middle line:84%
And he eventually has the
motivation and the essence

00:43:54.580 --> 00:43:55.780 align:middle line:90%
to say, well, wait a minute.

00:43:55.780 --> 00:43:58.510 align:middle line:84%
Actually, I have become too
unbalanced on both sides.

00:43:58.510 --> 00:44:01.360 align:middle line:84%
The trick is to walk the
fine line in between the two.

00:44:01.360 --> 00:44:04.360 align:middle line:84%
That's the secret of doing
this properly-- the light

00:44:04.360 --> 00:44:05.910 align:middle line:84%
and the dark, being
aware of both,

00:44:05.910 --> 00:44:08.710 align:middle line:84%
and knowing when to
apply both, and also

00:44:08.710 --> 00:44:11.200 align:middle line:84%
to walk the fine line in
between, very hard to do.

00:44:11.200 --> 00:44:12.700 align:middle line:84%
And you know who's doing it
because they usually have

00:44:12.700 --> 00:44:13.908 align:middle line:90%
all the arrows on their back.

00:44:13.908 --> 00:44:15.610 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Right,
no, exactly, it's

00:44:15.610 --> 00:44:18.780 align:middle line:84%
as though the pressure
between the two, as you say,

00:44:18.780 --> 00:44:22.680 align:middle line:84%
we'll make a decision that
kind of tips us over into one.

00:44:22.680 --> 00:44:24.480 align:middle line:84%
And then the
self-correcting mechanism

00:44:24.480 --> 00:44:27.300 align:middle line:84%
is the pain from, say, if you've
tipped over into the dark.

00:44:27.300 --> 00:44:29.700 align:middle line:84%
Ultimately, you can
self-correct and move back

00:44:29.700 --> 00:44:30.700 align:middle line:90%
over the other way.

00:44:30.700 --> 00:44:32.730 align:middle line:84%
But then if you're lost
in the clouds again,

00:44:32.730 --> 00:44:36.660 align:middle line:84%
you're ineffective, and you're
really not using your will

00:44:36.660 --> 00:44:39.160 align:middle line:84%
and your abilities on the
planet at the same time.

00:44:39.160 --> 00:44:41.250 align:middle line:84%
So you have to take that
light and, as you say,

00:44:41.250 --> 00:44:45.300 align:middle line:84%
focus it in this scene right
between light and dark.

00:44:45.300 --> 00:44:50.280 align:middle line:84%
And I think that a lot of the
misunderstanding on the planet

00:44:50.280 --> 00:44:53.730 align:middle line:84%
is really about where you
choose to put your focus.

00:44:53.730 --> 00:44:55.419 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: Exactly,
or over-associating

00:44:55.419 --> 00:44:57.960 align:middle line:84%
with a particular concept, where
you lose track of everything

00:44:57.960 --> 00:45:00.812 align:middle line:84%
else, kind of almost like being
lost in love with somebody.

00:45:00.812 --> 00:45:03.020 align:middle line:84%
It's wonderful, but you also
lose track of the bigger

00:45:03.020 --> 00:45:04.510 align:middle line:90%
picture around you.

00:45:04.510 --> 00:45:05.670 align:middle line:90%
And it's also just energy.

00:45:05.670 --> 00:45:07.720 align:middle line:84%
Energy doesn't give a
damn about anything.

00:45:07.720 --> 00:45:08.860 align:middle line:90%
It's just energy.

00:45:08.860 --> 00:45:11.790 align:middle line:84%
It's your intent that you
give this energy that gives it

00:45:11.790 --> 00:45:15.150 align:middle line:84%
the direction, which is actually
kind of interesting because it

00:45:15.150 --> 00:45:17.010 align:middle line:84%
brings up the concept
of the Templar logo,

00:45:17.010 --> 00:45:20.370 align:middle line:84%
you know, with the two knights
riding one horse, which

00:45:20.370 --> 00:45:22.830 align:middle line:84%
a lot of mainstream
historians will say,

00:45:22.830 --> 00:45:26.880 align:middle line:84%
well, they were so poor that two
knights had to ride one horse.

00:45:26.880 --> 00:45:29.310 align:middle line:10%
Well, any military
person will look at this

00:45:29.310 --> 00:45:31.410 align:middle line:10%
and say, how
absolutely ridiculous

00:45:31.410 --> 00:45:34.260 align:middle line:10%
to take two people weighing
down a horse going into battle?

00:45:34.260 --> 00:45:35.640 align:middle line:10%
Of course, it's a symbol.

00:45:35.640 --> 00:45:38.190 align:middle line:10%
The horse is the
symbol of knowledge.

00:45:38.190 --> 00:45:41.480 align:middle line:10%
It's literally the Western
equivalent of the Sphinx.

00:45:41.480 --> 00:45:43.900 align:middle line:10%
It's the symbol of knowledge.

00:45:43.900 --> 00:45:46.530 align:middle line:10%
So when you have two
people riding one horse,

00:45:46.530 --> 00:45:49.420 align:middle line:10%
that's the twin sides of
personality, the light

00:45:49.420 --> 00:45:50.310 align:middle line:10%
and the dark.

00:45:50.310 --> 00:45:52.900 align:middle line:84%
When you know that there's
a balance between the two

00:45:52.900 --> 00:45:54.450 align:middle line:84%
and you ride the
horse of knowledge,

00:45:54.450 --> 00:45:56.241 align:middle line:84%
you guide that horse
to where it's supposed

00:45:56.241 --> 00:45:57.670 align:middle line:90%
to go in this right direction.

00:45:57.670 --> 00:46:00.390 align:middle line:84%
That's what the true symbol of
the Templars riding the horse

00:46:00.390 --> 00:46:01.460 align:middle line:90%
is all about.

00:46:01.460 --> 00:46:04.500 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Well, and,
of course, you know,

00:46:04.500 --> 00:46:06.750 align:middle line:84%
we want to applaud those who
are riding on the, quote,

00:46:06.750 --> 00:46:07.800 align:middle line:90%
"side of light."

00:46:07.800 --> 00:46:11.100 align:middle line:84%
And we want to demonize those
riding on the side of dark.

00:46:11.100 --> 00:46:15.330 align:middle line:84%
But the reality is
each of these entities

00:46:15.330 --> 00:46:17.950 align:middle line:90%
is on their own path of growth.

00:46:17.950 --> 00:46:22.140 align:middle line:84%
They're providing their
own beingness or service,

00:46:22.140 --> 00:46:26.200 align:middle line:84%
whatever you want to call it,
to whatever realm they live in.

00:46:26.200 --> 00:46:30.180 align:middle line:84%
And so we can say that certainly
the dark has a purpose because

00:46:30.180 --> 00:46:34.320 align:middle line:84%
by the sheer contrast
and pain, you

00:46:34.320 --> 00:46:36.300 align:middle line:84%
can find your way
back into something

00:46:36.300 --> 00:46:38.540 align:middle line:84%
that's going to perhaps work
a little better for you,

00:46:38.540 --> 00:46:41.010 align:middle line:84%
you know, puts you into a
little higher frequency range.

00:46:41.010 --> 00:46:41.430 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: They put
you into perspective.

00:46:41.430 --> 00:46:43.020 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: On the other
hand, those very same beings

00:46:43.020 --> 00:46:44.580 align:middle line:84%
are learning from
that that they're

00:46:44.580 --> 00:46:46.780 align:middle line:90%
witnessing in you as well.

00:46:46.780 --> 00:46:49.270 align:middle line:90%
And so it's nothing but growth.

00:46:49.270 --> 00:46:52.320 align:middle line:84%
I think if we can look
at it more as nothing

00:46:52.320 --> 00:46:55.200 align:middle line:84%
but growth on both sides,
neither finish growing.

00:46:55.200 --> 00:46:56.502 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Oh, you never do.

00:46:56.502 --> 00:46:57.460 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: You never do.

00:46:57.460 --> 00:46:58.320 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: And the
Templars were very

00:46:58.320 --> 00:46:59.385 align:middle line:84%
aware of this,
when you recognize

00:46:59.385 --> 00:47:01.876 align:middle line:84%
there were so many of them
that later on during the end

00:47:01.876 --> 00:47:04.500 align:middle line:84%
stages of the Templar movement,
when they were all being burned

00:47:04.500 --> 00:47:06.749 align:middle line:84%
alive at the stake, a lot
of them went to their deaths

00:47:06.749 --> 00:47:09.302 align:middle line:84%
actually smiling
because they understood.

00:47:09.302 --> 00:47:11.010 align:middle line:84%
And one of the things
that you are taught

00:47:11.010 --> 00:47:13.380 align:middle line:84%
in the inner brotherhood
of the Templars

00:47:13.380 --> 00:47:16.530 align:middle line:84%
and the people like them
was the manipulation

00:47:16.530 --> 00:47:18.480 align:middle line:84%
of matter and
energy and emotion,

00:47:18.480 --> 00:47:21.570 align:middle line:84%
which is energy in motion,
once you understand

00:47:21.570 --> 00:47:23.910 align:middle line:84%
to disengage yourself from
the emotion of things,

00:47:23.910 --> 00:47:27.300 align:middle line:84%
you have a degree of control,
like a rishi in India

00:47:27.300 --> 00:47:31.720 align:middle line:84%
or a yogi, that pain is
really a very temporal thing.

00:47:31.720 --> 00:47:34.300 align:middle line:84%
If you can just learn to
overcome that pain as you're

00:47:34.300 --> 00:47:35.699 align:middle line:84%
being burned alive,
you recognize

00:47:35.699 --> 00:47:37.990 align:middle line:84%
there's a moment where it's
going to hurt a little bit.

00:47:37.990 --> 00:47:39.198 align:middle line:90%
And then you've crossed over.

00:47:39.198 --> 00:47:41.280 align:middle line:84%
And you're now on a
different level of reality.

00:47:41.280 --> 00:47:43.110 align:middle line:84%
And you can actually
influence things here

00:47:43.110 --> 00:47:44.467 align:middle line:90%
on the physical world.

00:47:44.467 --> 00:47:46.800 align:middle line:84%
So for them, being burned
alive was actually a blessing.

00:47:46.800 --> 00:47:49.559 align:middle line:84%
They said, well, the Earth
is just a temporary stage

00:47:49.559 --> 00:47:50.850 align:middle line:90%
on the bigger scheme of things.

00:47:50.850 --> 00:47:52.620 align:middle line:84%
They already understood
these old concepts.

00:47:52.620 --> 00:47:54.036 align:middle line:84%
So for them, it
wasn't a big deal.

00:47:54.036 --> 00:47:55.770 align:middle line:84%
They were not leaving
anything behind

00:47:55.770 --> 00:47:58.061 align:middle line:84%
because they had already
renounced their worldly goods.

00:47:58.061 --> 00:47:59.640 align:middle line:84%
They weren't
possessive of anything.

00:47:59.640 --> 00:48:03.210 align:middle line:84%
They recognized the
transient nature of reality.

00:48:03.210 --> 00:48:05.370 align:middle line:84%
So for them, the
material position

00:48:05.370 --> 00:48:08.402 align:middle line:84%
that they held in this world and
going to their death for them

00:48:08.402 --> 00:48:09.610 align:middle line:90%
really didn't mean that much.

00:48:09.610 --> 00:48:11.430 align:middle line:84%
They said, well, we're about
to go on another adventure.

00:48:11.430 --> 00:48:12.340 align:middle line:90%
See ya.

00:48:12.340 --> 00:48:14.548 align:middle line:84%
We'll meet you on the other
side as well, by the way.

00:48:14.548 --> 00:48:16.180 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Right,
and we'll be back.

00:48:16.180 --> 00:48:16.530 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: We'll be back.

00:48:16.530 --> 00:48:17.360 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHTER]

00:48:17.360 --> 00:48:18.160 align:middle line:90%


00:48:18.160 --> 00:48:19.430 align:middle line:90%
We'll be back as [INAUDIBLE]

00:48:19.430 --> 00:48:21.459 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Exactly,
or something, right.

00:48:21.459 --> 00:48:22.875 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: Or the
Invisible College,

00:48:22.875 --> 00:48:24.394 align:middle line:90%
as they were called in France.

00:48:24.394 --> 00:48:26.810 align:middle line:84%
I mean, they keep regurgitating
themselves again and again

00:48:26.810 --> 00:48:27.712 align:middle line:90%
and again.

00:48:27.712 --> 00:48:29.670 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: Yes, OK, let's
get to the punch line.

00:48:29.670 --> 00:48:31.120 align:middle line:90%
Let's talk about the Grail now.

00:48:31.120 --> 00:48:31.920 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: The Grail.

00:48:31.920 --> 00:48:33.205 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Mm-hmm.

00:48:33.205 --> 00:48:34.830 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: Now, you
know, I really didn't

00:48:34.830 --> 00:48:36.960 align:middle line:90%
want to go there in the book.

00:48:36.960 --> 00:48:39.360 align:middle line:84%
It's almost like anathema
to any historian.

00:48:39.360 --> 00:48:41.790 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, maybe I
just didn't have the depth

00:48:41.790 --> 00:48:44.415 align:middle line:84%
to go into the Grail because so
much had been written about it.

00:48:44.415 --> 00:48:46.300 align:middle line:84%
But inevitably, you
stroke the Templar urn,

00:48:46.300 --> 00:48:49.140 align:middle line:84%
and out comes the
genie with the Grail.

00:48:49.140 --> 00:48:52.830 align:middle line:84%
And so, you know, this is why
the book took so long to write.

00:48:52.830 --> 00:48:54.515 align:middle line:84%
I had to go back
and relearn stuff,

00:48:54.515 --> 00:48:56.640 align:middle line:84%
and I had to see it from
a different point of view.

00:48:56.640 --> 00:48:58.110 align:middle line:10%
And the oldest
mention of the Grail

00:48:58.110 --> 00:49:00.940 align:middle line:10%
is actually in Sumeria,
the "Song of Inanna,"

00:49:00.940 --> 00:49:03.780 align:middle line:10%
which becomes a blueprint
for the "Song of Solomon."

00:49:03.780 --> 00:49:05.670 align:middle line:84%
And in the "Song of
Inanna," they talk about

00:49:05.670 --> 00:49:08.780 align:middle line:84%
the [NON-ENGLISH],, which is
where the word comes from.

00:49:08.780 --> 00:49:11.640 align:middle line:84%
And the [NON-ENGLISH]
essentially is symbolized

00:49:11.640 --> 00:49:15.150 align:middle line:84%
by this divine virgin holding
a ceremonial tray called

00:49:15.150 --> 00:49:19.540 align:middle line:84%
a salver, upon which sits
this gold-silver object.

00:49:19.540 --> 00:49:22.030 align:middle line:84%
And I'm looking at this, and
I'm going, wait a minute.

00:49:22.030 --> 00:49:23.730 align:middle line:84%
Everything being
equal in the mysteries

00:49:23.730 --> 00:49:25.780 align:middle line:90%
teachings, this is all a symbol.

00:49:25.780 --> 00:49:28.270 align:middle line:84%
That woman represents
the divine virgin.

00:49:28.270 --> 00:49:30.610 align:middle line:84%
She is holding a ceremonial
tray made of silver.

00:49:30.610 --> 00:49:34.210 align:middle line:90%
And the Grail is a gold cup.

00:49:34.210 --> 00:49:37.447 align:middle line:84%
That's an Egyptian concept
between the matter of the moon

00:49:37.447 --> 00:49:39.280 align:middle line:84%
and the sun, the masculine
and the feminine,

00:49:39.280 --> 00:49:42.410 align:middle line:84%
the two elements that make up
the top of all the pyramids,

00:49:42.410 --> 00:49:43.630 align:middle line:90%
you know.

00:49:43.630 --> 00:49:43.915 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Isis-Osiris.

00:49:43.915 --> 00:49:46.206 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: I thought, so perhaps
what we're talking about

00:49:46.206 --> 00:49:48.130 align:middle line:90%
is not a real object.

00:49:48.130 --> 00:49:51.130 align:middle line:84%
But ironically and
paradoxically, actually, it

00:49:51.130 --> 00:49:54.310 align:middle line:84%
is, because the people that
held that understanding were

00:49:54.310 --> 00:49:56.920 align:middle line:84%
the holy bloodline, the
priestesses of the temple,

00:49:56.920 --> 00:49:59.590 align:middle line:84%
who, of course, was
Inanna, the woman in red,

00:49:59.590 --> 00:50:02.590 align:middle line:84%
who then through time,
eventually ends up the baton

00:50:02.590 --> 00:50:04.330 align:middle line:90%
gets handed to Mary Magdalene.

00:50:04.330 --> 00:50:05.770 align:middle line:84%
And she eventually
goes to France

00:50:05.770 --> 00:50:07.720 align:middle line:84%
and communicates with
the people in France,

00:50:07.720 --> 00:50:10.440 align:middle line:84%
transmits the information,
continues the holy bloodline

00:50:10.440 --> 00:50:11.780 align:middle line:90%
in that part of the world.

00:50:11.780 --> 00:50:13.960 align:middle line:84%
The Templars picked
up on this, of course.

00:50:13.960 --> 00:50:16.150 align:middle line:84%
And they basically
are the reason

00:50:16.150 --> 00:50:18.490 align:middle line:84%
that the only way to bring
this all back into focus

00:50:18.490 --> 00:50:21.510 align:middle line:84%
is to recreate the
Grail in Portugal.

00:50:21.510 --> 00:50:23.990 align:middle line:90%
And I still remember the day.

00:50:23.990 --> 00:50:25.710 align:middle line:84%
15 years later,
and I'm thinking,

00:50:25.710 --> 00:50:28.170 align:middle line:84%
there's something very
obvious that I'm missing here.

00:50:28.170 --> 00:50:30.500 align:middle line:10%
And I'm sitting in this
wonderful courtyard

00:50:30.500 --> 00:50:32.160 align:middle line:10%
near the Rotunda of Tomar.

00:50:32.160 --> 00:50:33.830 align:middle line:10%
And the rotunda is
talking back to me.

00:50:33.830 --> 00:50:34.630 align:middle line:10%
And trust me.

00:50:34.630 --> 00:50:36.160 align:middle line:10%
It really does happen.

00:50:36.160 --> 00:50:38.590 align:middle line:10%
And it says, well,
why don't you actually

00:50:38.590 --> 00:50:40.311 align:middle line:10%
find out what my
original name is?

00:50:40.311 --> 00:50:42.060 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, I'd
better write this down.

00:50:42.060 --> 00:50:43.215 align:middle line:90%
This could be interesting.

00:50:43.215 --> 00:50:44.590 align:middle line:84%
And I found out
the original name

00:50:44.590 --> 00:50:46.423 align:middle line:84%
for the rotunda, which
is a word that exists

00:50:46.423 --> 00:50:47.730 align:middle line:90%
in Portuguese by the way--

00:50:47.730 --> 00:50:49.146 align:middle line:84%
and it means the
same things as it

00:50:49.146 --> 00:50:50.890 align:middle line:84%
does in English
and in Latin, which

00:50:50.890 --> 00:50:55.040 align:middle line:84%
is a round building, which never
had an altar, never had a door.

00:50:55.040 --> 00:50:57.979 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, why wouldn't they
have just called it a rotunda?

00:50:57.979 --> 00:50:59.520 align:middle line:84%
They called it a
[PORTUGUESE],, which

00:50:59.520 --> 00:51:01.200 align:middle line:84%
is a very unusual
word in Portuguese.

00:51:01.200 --> 00:51:03.640 align:middle line:84%
So, you know, a
simple dictionary,

00:51:03.640 --> 00:51:05.890 align:middle line:84%
you go and find out
what's this all about.

00:51:05.890 --> 00:51:08.297 align:middle line:90%
It turns out the [PORTUGUESE]--

00:51:08.297 --> 00:51:10.630 align:middle line:84%
here is a big spoiler, if
you're going to read the book.

00:51:10.630 --> 00:51:12.850 align:middle line:90%
So don't hear this right now.

00:51:12.850 --> 00:51:16.450 align:middle line:84%
[PORTUGUESE] literally means
a salver, a ceremonial tray.

00:51:16.450 --> 00:51:19.030 align:middle line:84%
And that's where the
penny suddenly drops.

00:51:19.030 --> 00:51:21.310 align:middle line:84%
Why would you call a
building, a round building,

00:51:21.310 --> 00:51:24.250 align:middle line:84%
a ceremonial tray,
unless, of course, my God,

00:51:24.250 --> 00:51:25.720 align:middle line:90%
the building is the Grail.

00:51:25.720 --> 00:51:26.860 align:middle line:90%
But it's not the building.

00:51:26.860 --> 00:51:30.010 align:middle line:84%
It's the action that takes
place inside the building, which

00:51:30.010 --> 00:51:33.750 align:middle line:84%
we now know was deliberately
sited on a hot spot of energy

00:51:33.750 --> 00:51:36.180 align:middle line:84%
with specific
geometry to elucidate

00:51:36.180 --> 00:51:39.280 align:middle line:84%
a certain state of mind,
which was recreated

00:51:39.280 --> 00:51:42.040 align:middle line:84%
in a secret chamber where
the inner brotherhood did

00:51:42.040 --> 00:51:44.189 align:middle line:90%
their most secret initiation.

00:51:44.189 --> 00:51:45.230 align:middle line:90%
That's what it was about.

00:51:45.230 --> 00:51:47.930 align:middle line:84%
So the Grail technically
is in Portugal.

00:51:47.930 --> 00:51:49.600 align:middle line:84%
And yet it's also
everywhere else

00:51:49.600 --> 00:51:51.100 align:middle line:90%
where the Templars existed.

00:51:51.100 --> 00:51:53.290 align:middle line:84%
And it's also in any
other sacred site

00:51:53.290 --> 00:51:55.930 align:middle line:84%
where you connect with
the same sacred geometry,

00:51:55.930 --> 00:51:58.630 align:middle line:84%
the same designs, and
the same principles

00:51:58.630 --> 00:52:00.220 align:middle line:90%
which the Templars had designed.

00:52:00.220 --> 00:52:02.134 align:middle line:84%
So the Grail actually
is everywhere.

00:52:02.134 --> 00:52:03.550 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: I found
that fascinating

00:52:03.550 --> 00:52:06.490 align:middle line:84%
because then the stories
start making sense.

00:52:06.490 --> 00:52:08.770 align:middle line:84%
And Jim Marrs' book, I don't
remember the name of it,

00:52:08.770 --> 00:52:13.750 align:middle line:84%
one I read many years ago about
the Scottish Rite Templars

00:52:13.750 --> 00:52:17.590 align:middle line:84%
housing the Grail, you know,
and then that the Grail had gone

00:52:17.590 --> 00:52:20.770 align:middle line:84%
to America and all
these different tales

00:52:20.770 --> 00:52:24.520 align:middle line:84%
I've read over the last
15, 20 years about who

00:52:24.520 --> 00:52:25.900 align:middle line:90%
houses the Grail.

00:52:25.900 --> 00:52:27.284 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: A lot of people.

00:52:27.284 --> 00:52:29.200 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: This is the
first time it's actually

00:52:29.200 --> 00:52:31.620 align:middle line:84%
made sense, including
under the Temple Mount.

00:52:31.620 --> 00:52:33.370 align:middle line:10%
>>SILVA: Including
under the Temple Mount,

00:52:33.370 --> 00:52:35.410 align:middle line:10%
exactly, including
under the Great Pyramid,

00:52:35.410 --> 00:52:38.380 align:middle line:10%
including under the Great
Pyramids of Chichen Itza

00:52:38.380 --> 00:52:40.630 align:middle line:10%
and the Pyramid of the
Magician, next to Chichen Itza,

00:52:40.630 --> 00:52:41.960 align:middle line:10%
which no one pays attention to.

00:52:41.960 --> 00:52:42.760 align:middle line:90%
It's everywhere.

00:52:42.760 --> 00:52:44.160 align:middle line:90%
It's a concept.

00:52:44.160 --> 00:52:46.930 align:middle line:84%
It's literally the meeting
of the heart and the mind.

00:52:46.930 --> 00:52:49.300 align:middle line:10%
The ultimate aim of
the spiritual initiate

00:52:49.300 --> 00:52:53.390 align:middle line:10%
is to basically
find him or herself.

00:52:53.390 --> 00:52:56.140 align:middle line:84%
So it's an object
insofar as it's

00:52:56.140 --> 00:52:58.329 align:middle line:84%
represented by a
cup that is filled

00:52:58.329 --> 00:52:59.870 align:middle line:84%
with the bloodline
of the people that

00:52:59.870 --> 00:53:02.260 align:middle line:84%
maintained that understanding,
but it's not an object.

00:53:02.260 --> 00:53:04.600 align:middle line:84%
If you're seeking an object,
you've lost the plot.

00:53:04.600 --> 00:53:06.250 align:middle line:90%
This is not about object things.

00:53:06.250 --> 00:53:07.720 align:middle line:90%
It's not about physical things.

00:53:07.720 --> 00:53:09.520 align:middle line:90%
It's about a spiritual concept.

00:53:09.520 --> 00:53:11.330 align:middle line:84%
Now you're on the
right line of inquiry.

00:53:11.330 --> 00:53:12.910 align:middle line:84%
This is a thing
that the Templars

00:53:12.910 --> 00:53:14.890 align:middle line:90%
would protect to their death.

00:53:14.890 --> 00:53:17.590 align:middle line:84%
And they said, we will
protect the greatest secret

00:53:17.590 --> 00:53:20.212 align:middle line:84%
within our brotherhood
to the death

00:53:20.212 --> 00:53:21.670 align:middle line:84%
because they didn't
want this stuff

00:53:21.670 --> 00:53:24.730 align:middle line:84%
to be given to anybody who
would misuse this understanding.

00:53:24.730 --> 00:53:29.020 align:middle line:84%
You had to be a very
spiritualized, balanced person

00:53:29.020 --> 00:53:31.120 align:middle line:84%
to just understand
the concept of what

00:53:31.120 --> 00:53:34.420 align:middle line:84%
it means to be a truly risen
and spiritualized initiate.

00:53:34.420 --> 00:53:36.640 align:middle line:90%
Jesus knew that.

00:53:36.640 --> 00:53:39.320 align:middle line:84%
He was following on from people
like Zoroaster and Mithra,

00:53:39.320 --> 00:53:42.860 align:middle line:84%
all these resurrected
god-men, Osiris, symbols

00:53:42.860 --> 00:53:44.200 align:middle line:90%
to this very day.

00:53:44.200 --> 00:53:47.150 align:middle line:84%
That was why they maintained
the secret to the very death

00:53:47.150 --> 00:53:49.510 align:middle line:84%
and why Templars,
or people wishing

00:53:49.510 --> 00:53:51.817 align:middle line:84%
to join the Templar
Order, and specifically

00:53:51.817 --> 00:53:54.400 align:middle line:84%
the inner brotherhood, which was
very different from the outer

00:53:54.400 --> 00:53:56.410 align:middle line:84%
brotherhood-- they just
did the menial stuff.

00:53:56.410 --> 00:53:58.790 align:middle line:84%
The inner brotherhood, they
were a ministerial college,

00:53:58.790 --> 00:53:59.610 align:middle line:90%
basically.

00:53:59.610 --> 00:54:01.480 align:middle line:90%
They were Essenes, essentially.

00:54:01.480 --> 00:54:05.260 align:middle line:84%
They had to declare a vow to
discover the joys of paradise.

00:54:05.260 --> 00:54:07.810 align:middle line:84%
And like I said, people
who want to go into battle

00:54:07.810 --> 00:54:11.410 align:middle line:84%
don't say things like that
unless joining the Templars

00:54:11.410 --> 00:54:13.150 align:middle line:90%
came with a spiritual benefit.

00:54:13.150 --> 00:54:14.740 align:middle line:84%
And that's where
it all made sense,

00:54:14.740 --> 00:54:17.670 align:middle line:84%
that the pursuit of the
Grail, this treasure, which

00:54:17.670 --> 00:54:19.955 align:middle line:84%
was a book of
information, that's

00:54:19.955 --> 00:54:21.330 align:middle line:84%
what they were
trying to protect.

00:54:21.330 --> 00:54:24.060 align:middle line:84%
It was about the treasure
that enabled the initiate

00:54:24.060 --> 00:54:26.552 align:middle line:84%
to discover his or
her gold within.

00:54:26.552 --> 00:54:28.760 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And this points
back to your previous work,

00:54:28.760 --> 00:54:30.570 align:middle line:90%
"The Lost Art of Resurrection."

00:54:30.570 --> 00:54:31.860 align:middle line:90%
>>SILVA: Exactly.

00:54:31.860 --> 00:54:33.280 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Go ahead.

00:54:33.280 --> 00:54:34.947 align:middle line:84%
We've got just a
couple of minutes left.

00:54:34.947 --> 00:54:37.071 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: I thought, what
am I doing this Wednesday?

00:54:37.071 --> 00:54:38.426 align:middle line:90%
Hey, that's a good story.

00:54:38.426 --> 00:54:41.070 align:middle line:84%
No, it led me to then
question the concept

00:54:41.070 --> 00:54:42.540 align:middle line:90%
of Jesus's resurrection.

00:54:42.540 --> 00:54:44.670 align:middle line:84%
Why were the early
Christians, the Gnostics,

00:54:44.670 --> 00:54:48.887 align:middle line:84%
being killed, massacred
by the fundamentalists?

00:54:48.887 --> 00:54:50.220 align:middle line:90%
And they nearly won, by the way.

00:54:50.220 --> 00:54:53.130 align:middle line:90%
It was a very, very close fight.

00:54:53.130 --> 00:54:57.270 align:middle line:84%
And I began to look into the
concepts of the apostle Thomas

00:54:57.270 --> 00:54:59.220 align:middle line:84%
and the writings of
Philip, the ones that

00:54:59.220 --> 00:55:00.840 align:middle line:90%
didn't make it into the Bible.

00:55:00.840 --> 00:55:03.600 align:middle line:84%
And, oh, Susannah, we're
talking about two very different

00:55:03.600 --> 00:55:06.570 align:middle line:84%
stories here because they're
talking about the whole concept

00:55:06.570 --> 00:55:08.220 align:middle line:90%
that the church is an impostor.

00:55:08.220 --> 00:55:10.960 align:middle line:84%
They have taken the place of
the true Christian brotherhood.

00:55:10.960 --> 00:55:11.760 align:middle line:90%
Wait a minute.

00:55:11.760 --> 00:55:12.885 align:middle line:90%
I was raised as a Catholic.

00:55:12.885 --> 00:55:14.739 align:middle line:84%
Where does this
come onto question?

00:55:14.739 --> 00:55:16.530 align:middle line:84%
And the Essenes were
saying the same thing,

00:55:16.530 --> 00:55:18.580 align:middle line:84%
and the Mandaeans were
saying the same thing.

00:55:18.580 --> 00:55:22.290 align:middle line:84%
And essentially, they were
protecting a very old concept

00:55:22.290 --> 00:55:23.190 align:middle line:90%
of spirituality.

00:55:23.190 --> 00:55:26.310 align:middle line:84%
It was an inner concept,
and it was about the idea

00:55:26.310 --> 00:55:29.850 align:middle line:84%
that the true concept of
living Resurrection never

00:55:29.850 --> 00:55:33.330 align:middle line:84%
had anyone dying, never had
anyone being nailed to a cross.

00:55:33.330 --> 00:55:36.490 align:middle line:84%
It was a metaphor
like anything else.

00:55:36.490 --> 00:55:38.400 align:middle line:84%
And the idea was that
you would undertake

00:55:38.400 --> 00:55:40.730 align:middle line:84%
this secret initiation for
which you would give up

00:55:40.730 --> 00:55:42.085 align:middle line:90%
three years of your life.

00:55:42.085 --> 00:55:44.190 align:middle line:90%
And you discard your property.

00:55:44.190 --> 00:55:45.750 align:middle line:90%
You put it into escrow.

00:55:45.750 --> 00:55:47.400 align:middle line:90%
You would wear white robes.

00:55:47.400 --> 00:55:48.560 align:middle line:90%
You do a ritual baptism.

00:55:48.560 --> 00:55:49.840 align:middle line:90%
Sound familiar?

00:55:49.840 --> 00:55:52.710 align:middle line:84%
And then you would
undertake a final act

00:55:52.710 --> 00:55:54.330 align:middle line:84%
where you go into
a secret chamber

00:55:54.330 --> 00:55:56.100 align:middle line:90%
under a specific building.

00:55:56.100 --> 00:55:59.700 align:middle line:84%
You were guided by a priestess
who would give you a narcotic.

00:55:59.700 --> 00:56:03.000 align:middle line:84%
And it was usually undertaken
on the 21st of December.

00:56:03.000 --> 00:56:06.240 align:middle line:84%
Three days later, you would
come back into your living body

00:56:06.240 --> 00:56:08.880 align:middle line:84%
after having gone walk away
and AWOL in the other world.

00:56:08.880 --> 00:56:09.960 align:middle line:90%
You would return.

00:56:09.960 --> 00:56:12.540 align:middle line:84%
You would be taken out
onto this sacred mound.

00:56:12.540 --> 00:56:16.440 align:middle line:84%
And you were declared risen
from the dead, still today

00:56:16.440 --> 00:56:18.970 align:middle line:84%
practiced, metaphorically,
in the third degree

00:56:18.970 --> 00:56:20.077 align:middle line:90%
of Freemasonry.

00:56:20.077 --> 00:56:22.660 align:middle line:84%
And so this is exactly what the
concept of living resurrection

00:56:22.660 --> 00:56:24.010 align:middle line:90%
was all about.

00:56:24.010 --> 00:56:26.670 align:middle line:84%
>>REGINA: And this was part of
the work of John the Baptist.

00:56:26.670 --> 00:56:28.503 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: And John the
Baptist was practicing

00:56:28.503 --> 00:56:30.436 align:middle line:84%
exactly the same thing
because his lineage

00:56:30.436 --> 00:56:32.310 align:middle line:84%
goes all the way back
to the Sumerian priests

00:56:32.310 --> 00:56:34.710 align:middle line:90%
and priestesses.

00:56:34.710 --> 00:56:36.030 align:middle line:90%
It is mind-blowing, isn't it?

00:56:36.030 --> 00:56:37.420 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: It is mind-blowing.

00:56:37.420 --> 00:56:43.900 align:middle line:84%
And the book is so worth the
time, because it takes time.

00:56:43.900 --> 00:56:46.200 align:middle line:84%
You have to go through, and
you have to think about it

00:56:46.200 --> 00:56:48.642 align:middle line:84%
and process it and
put the dots together.

00:56:48.642 --> 00:56:49.850 align:middle line:90%
You're putting them together.

00:56:49.850 --> 00:56:52.410 align:middle line:84%
But you can't help yourself but
try to put the dots together

00:56:52.410 --> 00:56:53.730 align:middle line:90%
as you go along.

00:56:53.730 --> 00:56:54.900 align:middle line:90%
I did this all the time.

00:56:54.900 --> 00:56:56.430 align:middle line:84%
And then the next
page, boom, you

00:56:56.430 --> 00:56:58.337 align:middle line:90%
put the dots together for me.

00:56:58.337 --> 00:57:00.420 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: I actually did
it as a bit of an antidote

00:57:00.420 --> 00:57:01.360 align:middle line:90%
to today's society.

00:57:01.360 --> 00:57:04.140 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I watch people in
airport lounges and everywhere

00:57:04.140 --> 00:57:07.140 align:middle line:84%
losing and giving
their God-given ability

00:57:07.140 --> 00:57:09.910 align:middle line:84%
to a little piece of
glass and technology

00:57:09.910 --> 00:57:12.090 align:middle line:84%
that's about that big,
sitting there and doing this

00:57:12.090 --> 00:57:12.960 align:middle line:90%
all the time.

00:57:12.960 --> 00:57:15.360 align:middle line:84%
The first time in history,
we've given away our power

00:57:15.360 --> 00:57:17.640 align:middle line:90%
to a little device.

00:57:17.640 --> 00:57:20.940 align:middle line:84%
We're no longer thinking
and being interactive

00:57:20.940 --> 00:57:22.440 align:middle line:90%
with our surroundings.

00:57:22.440 --> 00:57:24.280 align:middle line:84%
And I see this as a
big Achilles' heel.

00:57:24.280 --> 00:57:27.120 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, I am
going to doggedly write

00:57:27.120 --> 00:57:28.950 align:middle line:84%
a book that is
difficult, that you

00:57:28.950 --> 00:57:31.064 align:middle line:84%
have to keep your eye
on the ball so well.

00:57:31.064 --> 00:57:31.980 align:middle line:90%
>>REGINA: Boy, do you.

00:57:31.980 --> 00:57:34.438 align:middle line:84%
>>SILVA: Because we're dealing
with three different periods

00:57:34.438 --> 00:57:36.300 align:middle line:84%
of time in three
